olicy-defaultTests.tentative.html", "testing/web-platform/tests/trusted-types/TrustedTypePolicyFactory-createPolicy-exposedTests.tentative.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null, null], "node": "3f59edce5ead7025c7311fcbf9245787f7cb3579", "parents": ["22443bed54851de378c4c998fe517248ecbe3ff2", "2b44d3e0c64c79c9376d3ce770da319cc1d72d01"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Nicolas Chevobbe \u003cnchevobbe@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1576844 - Add a tabDetached even in content-process spec. r=yulia.\n\nThis event is sent from the content-process-connector in the server,\nand not having it declared in the spec was causing unknown packets\nerror messages.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D43587", "files": ["devtools/shared/specs/targets/content-process.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "a49a4f5227143c4aacf4ff69e7e8ae31946b5993", "parents": ["3f59edce5ead7025c7311fcbf9245787f7cb3579"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Daniel Holbert \u003cdholbert@cs.stanford.edu\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1575338 followup: Backed out changeset 243643e83bfc to reenable ink-skipping in WPT auto-margins-001.html.ini. (no review, just un-annotating a test)\n\nWe are pretty sure that this test no longer needs ink skipping to be disabled,\nas of bug 1574066.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D43642", "files": ["testing/web-platform/meta/css/css-flexbox/auto-margins-001.html.ini"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "68447f87ca05e2d5dc29258b594aa5cf028de829", "parents": ["a49a4f5227143c4aacf4ff69e7e8ae31946b5993"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Daniel Holbert \u003cdholbert@cs.stanford.edu\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1574031 followup: Backed out changeset eec51eb982bc to reenable ink-skipping in reftest decoration-style-standards.html. (no review, just reverting a test tweak)\n\nWe are pretty sure that this test no longer needs ink skipping to be disabled,\nas of bug 1574066.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D43643", "files": ["layout/reftests/text-decoration/decoration-style-standards-ref.html", "layout/reftests/text-decoration/decoration-style-standards.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "dd2e31e2f8338efa493a66821a2be11090048b3a", "parents": ["68447f87ca05e2d5dc29258b594aa5cf028de829"], "tags": []}, {"author": "lesley \u003clnorton@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1575955: Hide \"Sign in to Sync\" button when Sync is disabled. r=jaws\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D43508", "files": ["browser/components/aboutlogins/AboutLoginsParent.jsm", "browser/components/aboutlogins/content/aboutLogins.html", "browser/components/aboutlogins/content/components/fxaccounts-button.js", "browser/components/aboutlogins/tests/chrome/chrome.ini"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "9be49e3e9e296114be312d811d4f487951f81e0b", "parents": ["dd2e31e2f8338efa493a66821a2be11090048b3a"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Alex Rosenfeld \u003carosenfeld2003@mac.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1574053 - allow shift-click to disable column breakpoints.\n\nAllow user to disable column breakpoints with shift-click. Added mochitests to reinforce.   r=jlast.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D43326", "files": ["devtools/client/debugger/src/components/Editor/ColumnBreakpoint.js", "devtools/client/debugger/test/mochitest/browser_dbg-breakpoints-columns.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "b7d1b3ab0fb53cfed87544b46538241dae4eb181", "parents": ["9be49e3e9e296114be312d811d4f487951f81e0b"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Ehsan Akhgari \u003cehsan@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1540117 - Part 4: Fix browser_webconsole_trackingprotection_errors.js by ensuring that the test page does set a cookie. r=fix CLOSED TREE\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com//D43652", "files": ["devtools/client/webconsole/test/browser/browser.ini", "devtools/client/webconsole/test/browser/browser_webconsole_trackingprotection_errors.js", "devtools/client/webconsole/test/browser/cookieSetter.html", "devtools/client/webconsole/test/browser/test-trackingprotection-securityerrors.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "e30c654504e60a2224b1cf7efb31c0902ed459e1", "parents": ["b7d1b3ab0fb53cfed87544b46538241dae4eb181"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Krishnal Ciccolella \u003cshellyc23@hotmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1573316 - RDM controls are off-center (when in centered mode) r=gl\n\nAdded a CSS selector to aid in centering RDM controls\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D43067", "files": ["devtools/client/responsive/index.css"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "61bf21fe14164a7fb66ee5799a26e1128cce3fcf", "parents": ["e30c654504e60a2224b1cf7efb31c0902ed459e1"], "tags": []}, {"author": "L. David Baron \u003cdbaron@dbaron.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1576864 - Add reftest. r=emilio\n\n(Given that this was fixed quite a while ago, I didn't actually test\nthis in the reftest harness prior to the patch, but I did check that the\ntestcase fails in the browser on Firefox 68 release.)\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D43644", "files": ["layout/reftests/forms/fieldset/fieldset-height-resize-1-ref.html", "layout/reftests/forms/fieldset/fieldset-height-resize-1.html", "layout/reftests/forms/fieldset/reftest.list"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "cfeb7cdde492c8465d6a9e042d3f095d0324cc32", "parents": ["61bf21fe14164a7fb66ee5799a26e1128cce3fcf"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Nick Alexander \u003cnalexander@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1576707 - Allow \"absolute\" fetch artifacts to ignore `artifact_prefix`. r=aki\n\nThe way that `artifact-prefix` works is that it applies to the\n_consuming_ task's fetches... meaning that changing the prefix\nrequires working out the new paths for every fetch in the consuming\ntask.  This allows to \"opt-out\" of the artifact prefix mechanism for\nindividual fetches.\n\nDepends on D43534\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D43535", "files": ["taskcluster/taskgraph/transforms/job/__init__.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "4a7e698d5033d9703aa7e91d68ffe793d55a5a08", "parents": ["cfeb7cdde492c8465d6a9e042d3f095d0324cc32"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Ted Campbell \u003ctcampbell@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1576865 - Add missing call to ReportOutOfMemory in LazyScriptCreationData. r=jwalden\n\nThe closedOverBinding set uses the SystemAllocPolicy so we must manually\nraise OOM exceptions.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D43650", "files": ["js/src/frontend/SharedContext.h", "js/src/jit-test/tests/parser/bug-1576865-1.js", "js/src/jit-test/tests/parser/bug-1576865-2.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "48fe03f8728791a5a40e12d6223cacc2c2b4a96b", "parents": ["4a7e698d5033d9703aa7e91d68ffe793d55a5a08"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Alexandre Poirot \u003cpoirot.alex@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1576586 - Enable all about:debugging tests with fission. r=jdescottes,kmag\n\nAll these tests seem to work fine with Fission.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D43401", "files": ["devtools/client/aboutdebugging/test/browser/browser.ini"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "353399e8bf15d6b4c963dd3af5d8a2fe3059a931", "parents": ["48fe03f8728791a5a40e12d6223cacc2c2b4a96b"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Chris H-C \u003cchutten@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1570307 - Allow telemetry.batchDurationMS pref to be accessed on multiple threads. r=janerik\n\nWith the new StaticPrefsList (and possibly earlier?) prefs accessed on non-main\nthreads must now be atomic or assert-fail.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D43447", "files": ["modules/libpref/init/StaticPrefList.yaml"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "58e6e108dc33b2549179d4e2330cc2e01e95dabc", "parents": ["353399e8bf15d6b4c963dd3af5d8a2fe3059a931"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Chris H-C \u003cchutten@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1570307 - More GV Streaming Telemetry Tests r=janerik\n\nAdds:\n* Multiple Histogram test (nothing too interesting here)\n* Multiple Thread test (...)\n\nThe multithread test was a tricky one to get right, and even still I'm not\n100% convinced that it's testing contention properly enough to expose any\nthread-unsafety inside the batching accumulator.\n\nThat said, it does exercise the API on non-main threads, so I'm still calling\nit a win.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D43448", "files": ["toolkit/components/telemetry/Histograms.json", "toolkit/components/telemetry/geckoview/gtest/TestGeckoViewStreaming.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "64609c0ca2926dc0fe4e4561a50de6214324bf7b", "parents": ["58e6e108dc33b2549179d4e2330cc2e01e95dabc"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Gabriel Luong \u003cgabriel.luong@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1568157 - Part 3: Replace `toolbox.highlighter` with the contextual HighlighterFront. r=yulia\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D40316", "files": ["devtools/client/aboutdebugging/test/browser/browser_aboutdebugging_addons_debug_popup.js", "devtools/client/accessibility/components/Accessible.js", "devtools/client/debugger/panel.js", "devtools/client/dom/content/components/DomTree.js", "devtools/client/dom/test/browser_dom_nodes_highlight.js", "devtools/client/framework/components/ToolboxToolbar.js", "devtools/client/framework/toolbox.js", "devtools/client/inspector/animation/test/browser_animation_animation-target_highlight.js", "devtools/client/inspector/boxmodel/test/browser_boxmodel_guides.js", "devtools/client/inspector/extensions/extension-sidebar.js", "devtools/client/inspector/extensions/test/browser_inspector_extension_sidebar.js", "devtools/client/inspector/flexbox/test/browser_flexbox_container_element_rep.js", "devtools/client/inspector/grids/test/browser_grids_grid-list-element-rep.js", "devtools/client/inspector/inspector.js", "devtools/client/inspector/markup/markup.js", "devtools/client/inspector/markup/test/browser_markup_events_click_to_close.js", "devtools/client/inspector/test/browser_inspector_breadcrumbs_highlight_hover.js", "devtools/client/inspector/test/browser_inspector_breadcrumbs_keyboard_trap.js", "devtools/client/inspector/test/browser_inspector_highlighter-01.js", "devtools/client/inspector/test/browser_inspector_highlighter-hover_03.js", "devtools/client/inspector/test/shared-head.js", "devtools/client/shared/components/reps/reps-old.js", "devtools/client/shared/test/test-actor-registry.js", "devtools/client/shared/test/test-actor.js", "devtools/client/shared/widgets/VariablesView.jsm", "devtools/client/webconsole/test/browser/browser_webconsole_nodes_highlight.js", "devtools/client/webconsole/utils/object-inspector.js", "devtools/client/webconsole/webconsole-wrapper.js", "devtools/shared/fronts/node.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "c2546c971118620c7e6d527e0892807e8c6b0f2a", "parents": ["64609c0ca2926dc0fe4e4561a50de6214324bf7b"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Brindusan Cristian \u003ccbrindusan@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Backed out changeset 48fe03f87287 (bug 1576865) for spidermonkey bustages at bug-1576865-1.js:46:1. CLOSED TREE", "files": ["js/src/frontend/SharedContext.h", "js/src/jit-test/tests/parser/bug-1576865-1.js", "js/src/jit-test/tests/parser/bug-1576865-2.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "98d279815d44949d46d21b934fd8f3ab49600d2c", "parents": ["c2546c971118620c7e6d527e0892807e8c6b0f2a"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Brindusan Cristian \u003ccbrindusan@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Backed out changeset 4a7e698d5033 (bug 1576707) for linting failure on /job/__init__.py:242:33. CLOSED TREE", "files": ["taskcluster/taskgraph/transforms/job/__init__.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "97d70de52aec45bde0ce4f3d7e6001c979730d63", "parents": ["98d279815d44949d46d21b934fd8f3ab49600d2c"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Simon Giesecke \u003csgiesecke@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1571407 - Add initial code style document for DOM Workers & Storage team r=ttung,asuth,edenchuang\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D40617", "files": ["dom/docs/index.rst", "dom/docs/workersAndStorage/CodeStyle.rst", "dom/docs/workersAndStorage/index.rst"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "253ee438b626cc0286c02e77765f990c6b37939f", "parents": ["97d70de52aec45bde0ce4f3d7e6001c979730d63"], "tags": []}, {"author": "\u003cmsirringhaus\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1573381 - \"gtest MediaMIMETypes.MediaCodecs fails: Bug in MediaCodecs::ContainsPrefix()\". r=bvandyk", "files": ["dom/media/MediaMIMETypes.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "3d47c2d160a7ed1394f56211ca70b2f53f0e9750", "parents": ["253ee438b626cc0286c02e77765f990c6b37939f"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Ehsan Akhgari \u003cehsan@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1540117 - Part 5: Fix browser_webconsole_warning_group_content_blocking.js too by ensuring that the test image does set a cookie. r=fix CLOSED TREE\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com//D43671", "files": ["devtools/client/webconsole/test/browser/browser.ini", "devtools/client/webconsole/test/browser/browser_webconsole_warning_group_content_blocking.js", "devtools/client/webconsole/test/browser/test-image.png^headers^"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "c72fb6d63304f4b5df0dd05a3d2973b1fd4ee0da", "parents": ["3d47c2d160a7ed1394f56211ca70b2f53f0e9750"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Lina Cambridge \u003clina@yakshaving.ninja\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1576796 - Report local and remote tree sizes in bookmarks mirror shutdown hang crash reports. r=tcsc\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D43575", "files": ["toolkit/components/places/SyncedBookmarksMirror.jsm", "toolkit/components/places/tests/sync/test_bookmark_abort_merging.js", "toolkit/components/places/tests/sync/test_bookmark_structure_changes.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "6ead466a6fadee5eddf2c538122b1769977b00b9", "parents": ["c72fb6d63304f4b5df0dd05a3d2973b1fd4ee0da"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Lina Cambridge \u003clina@yakshaving.ninja\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1576810 - Avoid temp B-trees when fetching bookmarks mirror observer notifications. r=tcsc\n\nThe queries we use to fetch observer notifications need to sort all\nrows in every notification table. This is expensive, so this commit\navoids sorting by adding indexes on item levels to all tables, and\nremoving the parent and position from the `ORDER BY` clause in\nnon-test code.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D43576", "files": ["toolkit/components/places/SyncedBookmarksMirror.jsm", "toolkit/components/places/tests/sync/test_bookmark_observer_recorder.js", "toolkit/components/places/tests/sync/test_bookmark_structure_changes.js", "toolkit/components/places/tests/sync/test_bookmark_value_changes.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "0ea06b6d2f7fe0e58c9ffc12de435e3376df59ce", "parents": ["6ead466a6fadee5eddf2c538122b1769977b00b9"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Lina Cambridge \u003clina@yakshaving.ninja\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1575757 - Don't use `WITH RECURSIVE` to build the local tree. r=tcsc\n\nThis commit replaces the `localItems` CTE with a single table scan\nthat fetches item and structure info in one pass. It also adds a\n`structurePositions` index, so that fetching the remote structure can\nuse a covering index and avoid an extra sorting step.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D43577", "files": ["Cargo.lock", "third_party/rust/dogear/.cargo-checksum.json", "third_party/rust/dogear/Cargo.toml", "third_party/rust/dogear/src/merge.rs", "third_party/rust/dogear/src/tests.rs", "third_party/rust/dogear/src/tree.rs", "toolkit/components/places/SyncedBookmarksMirror.jsm", "toolkit/components/places/bookmark_sync/Cargo.toml", "toolkit/components/places/bookmark_sync/src/store.rs", "toolkit/components/places/tests/sync/test_bookmark_mirror_migration.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "7438ce6ba80cc644ce4d6dd77c59d6c844b75e05", "parents": ["0ea06b6d2f7fe0e58c9ffc12de435e3376df59ce"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Tomislav Jovanovic \u003ctomica@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1573045 - Use {restrictedSchemes: false} for tabs.query MatchPattern r=mixedpuppy\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D43602", "files": ["browser/components/extensions/parent/ext-tabs.js", "browser/components/extensions/test/browser/browser_ext_tabs_query.js", "mobile/android/components/extensions/ext-tabs.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "51f44b58102de2beaf3ef99133b8384329190ace", "parents": ["7438ce6ba80cc644ce4d6dd77c59d6c844b75e05"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Miko Mynttinen \u003cmikokm@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1576985 - Use RefPtr for hit test info AGR and ASR r=mattwoodrow\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D43661", "files": ["layout/painting/FrameLayerBuilder.cpp", "layout/painting/nsDisplayList.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "9fca488d4a860aa6f7326eba919f3cb4de514a3e", "parents": ["51f44b58102de2beaf3ef99133b8384329190ace"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Nihanth Subramanya \u003cnhnt11@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1576929 - [PanelMultiView] Ensure multi-line subview headers have enough padding. r=pbz\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D43620", "files": ["browser/themes/shared/customizableui/panelUI.inc.css"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "091580ce239fb367bb20702f37c5f8b80cdfd428", "parents": ["9fca488d4a860aa6f7326eba919f3cb4de514a3e"], "tags": []}, {"author": "longsonr \u003clongsonr@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1570799 - pass the original element into nsXMLContentSerializer::CheckElementEnd so that we can determine whether it has children properly r=hsivonen\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D43450", "files": ["dom/base/nsDocumentEncoder.cpp", "dom/base/nsHTMLContentSerializer.cpp", "dom/base/nsHTMLContentSerializer.h", "dom/base/nsIContentSerializer.h", "dom/base/nsPlainTextSerializer.cpp", "dom/base/nsPlainTextSerializer.h", "dom/base/nsXHTMLContentSerializer.cpp", "dom/base/nsXHTMLContentSerializer.h", "dom/base/nsXMLContentSerializer.cpp", "dom/base/nsXMLContentSerializer.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "97e6c7ca3b6bc8a8bd26cf8f9da3a19e780e0530", "parents": ["091580ce239fb367bb20702f37c5f8b80cdfd428"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Michael Kaply \u003cmozilla@kaply.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1573967 - Add policy to set the default rememberSignons policy. r=MattN,fluent-reviewers,flod\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D42715", "files": ["browser/components/enterprisepolicies/Policies.jsm", "browser/components/enterprisepolicies/schemas/policies-schema.json", "browser/components/enterprisepolicies/tests/xpcshell/test_simple_pref_policies.js", "browser/locales/en-US/browser/policies/policies-descriptions.ftl"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "45a0949f2d5dd8e46255d0be331dc5ddb57ed245", "parents": ["97e6c7ca3b6bc8a8bd26cf8f9da3a19e780e0530"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Mike Hommey \u003cmh+mozilla@glandium.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1575198 - Reenable cranelift on central. r=nalexander\n\nBug 1555894 disabled it for gecko builds, but since then bug 1576003\nand https://github.com/CraneStation/cranelift/pull/924 landed, which\nshould make its cost to the build less problematic.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D43581", "files": ["js/moz.configure"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "14a7894321177ca9c0e4b6fb7347e3f281fa6e92", "parents": ["45a0949f2d5dd8e46255d0be331dc5ddb57ed245"], "tags": []}, {"author": "David Walsh \u003cdwalsh@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1555333 - Toggle skipPausing when adding or enabling a breakpoint via reducers r=jlast\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D43512", "files": ["devtools/client/debugger/src/actions/pause/index.js", "devtools/client/debugger/src/actions/pause/skipPausing.js", "devtools/client/debugger/src/components/SecondaryPanes/DOMMutationBreakpoints.js", "devtools/client/debugger/src/reducers/pause.js", "devtools/client/debugger/test/mochitest/browser_dbg-breakpoint-skipping.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "c50fea61ff7079b8efc1b70a4f6c60ea24dc0b15", "parents": ["14a7894321177ca9c0e4b6fb7347e3f281fa6e92"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Sylvestre Ledru \u003csledru@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1575249 - Add a lint to check for source file permissions r=ahal\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D42672", "files": ["tools/lint/file-perm.yml", "tools/lint/file-perm/__init__.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "3076039dfbf4be60d0d90a011298770f2f2ec930", "parents": ["c50fea61ff7079b8efc1b70a4f6c60ea24dc0b15"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Sylvestre Ledru \u003csledru@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1575249 - Run the check for incorrect file permissions in the CI r=ahal\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D43362", "files": ["taskcluster/ci/source-test/mozlint.yml"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "cd3f609f008112adf2fdba0180bfe1bb9802cfe8", "parents": ["3076039dfbf4be60d0d90a011298770f2f2ec930"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Sylvestre Ledru \u003csledru@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1575250 - Add a lint to check for trailing white spaces and windows line return r=ahal\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D42675", "files": ["tools/lint/file-whitespace.yml", "tools/lint/file-whitespace/__init__.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "739c2eaf02feee215fee5197b0b5b3bbedcba7af", "parents": ["cd3f609f008112adf2fdba0180bfe1bb9802cfe8"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Sylvestre Ledru \u003csledru@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1575250 - Run the check for trailing whitespaces and Windows CR in the CI r=ahal\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D43360", "files": ["taskcluster/ci/source-test/mozlint.yml"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "689d2a67147048b5545b5a394c50087d175fcfba", "parents": ["739c2eaf02feee215fee5197b0b5b3bbedcba7af"], "tags": []}, {"author": "David Walsh \u003cdwalsh@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1576679 - Turn on inline preview by default r=jlast\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D43490", "files": ["devtools/client/debugger/src/actions/tests/pending-breakpoints.spec.js", "devtools/client/debugger/src/actions/types/UIAction.js", "devtools/client/debugger/src/actions/ui.js", "devtools/client/debugger/src/components/Editor/index.js", "devtools/client/debugger/src/components/Editor/menus/editor.js", "devtools/client/debugger/src/reducers/ui.js", "devtools/client/locales/en-US/debugger.properties", "devtools/client/preferences/debugger.js", "devtools/client/webconsole/test/browser/browser_webconsole_eval_in_debugger_stackframe.js", "devtools/client/webconsole/test/browser/browser_webconsole_eval_in_debugger_stackframe2.js", "devtools/client/webconsole/test/browser/browser_webconsole_object_inspector_while_debugging_and_inspecting.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "19cf8e37f2868369ee8ca86a81074b15b71b3dc8", "parents": ["689d2a67147048b5545b5a394c50087d175fcfba"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Tom Ritter \u003ctom@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1575975 - Enable the maintenance service for MinGW r=firefox-build-system-reviewers,mshal\n\nWe don't need to disable it. The problem with this commit is that\nwe want to keep the --disable-maintenance-service flag working, so\nwe might want a separate build for that (and other unusual --disable\nflags) - but such a build can be clearly labeled so people understand\nwhy things broke.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D43145", "files": ["browser/config/mozconfigs/win32/mingwclang", "browser/config/mozconfigs/win64/mingwclang", "toolkit/components/maintenanceservice/moz.build"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "663d87d66315567920932d793885182fcda014fe", "parents": ["19cf8e37f2868369ee8ca86a81074b15b71b3dc8"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Emilio Cobos \u00c1lvarez \u003cemilio@crisal.io\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1554498 - Don't use nsIMutationObserver for ShadowRoot. r=smaug\n\nThis penalizes a bit non-shadow-DOM content, in exchange of making Shadow DOM\nslightly faster as well.\n\nThe biggest advantage of this is that all ContentRemoved notifications would see\nthe flattened tree before the changes, which is something a11y needs to be\ncorrect.\n\nXBL would still not be handled right by a11y, but that's not new and content\ncannot do random stuff with XBL so it's not too bad.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D32639", "files": ["dom/base/CharacterData.cpp", "dom/base/Element.cpp", "dom/base/ShadowRoot.cpp", "dom/base/ShadowRoot.h", "dom/base/nsIContent.h", "dom/base/nsIContentInlines.h", "dom/html/HTMLSlotElement.cpp", "dom/html/HTMLSlotElement.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "2a619224d3799a1fe8f9a622bcab9e30ff4b5953", "parents": ["663d87d66315567920932d793885182fcda014fe"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Emilio Cobos \u00c1lvarez \u003cemilio@crisal.io\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1554498 - Fix an assertion that starts firing with the previous patch after addressing review feedback. r=smaug\n\nAfter addressing review comments in the other patch of this bug, debug builds\nassert all the time here when called from UnbindFromTree() on an already-unbound\nsubtree.\n\nWe clear the binding parent on unbind, so this is only guaranteed to match for\nconnected nodes, as far as I can tell.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D43641", "files": ["dom/base/Element.cpp", "dom/base/FragmentOrElement.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "43e96d7429198eecbbbb6241c0fc0cddc8f41442", "parents": ["2a619224d3799a1fe8f9a622bcab9e30ff4b5953"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Chris Manchester \u003ccmanchester@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1576737 - Add sccache-dist in offices docs to the tree. r=firefox-build-system-reviewers,mshal\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D43531", "files": ["build/docs/index.rst", "build/docs/sccache-dist.rst"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "9f0e21a3a418ec27f94b53f326b2e288e8fc730e", "parents": ["43e96d7429198eecbbbb6241c0fc0cddc8f41442"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Toshihito Kikuchi \u003ctkikuchi@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1575352 - Remove dynamic linking of urlmon for MinGW. r=aklotz\n\n4eca0f08c43b73dc1dd908fad58bdfd7f6973119 introduced dynamic linking of urlmon\nfor MinGW as a workaround.  Now that MinGW was updated, we can remove that\nworkaround.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D43281", "files": ["widget/windows/UrlmonHeaderOnlyUtils.h", "widget/windows/tests/TestUriValidation.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "137971f64c25356ca3a3a6e37fa879e301a4528f", "parents": ["9f0e21a3a418ec27f94b53f326b2e288e8fc730e"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Nick Alexander \u003cnalexander@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1576707 - Allow \"absolute\" fetch artifacts to ignore `artifact_prefix`. r=aki\n\nThe way that `artifact-prefix` works is that it applies to the\n_consuming_ task's fetches... meaning that changing the prefix\nrequires working out the new paths for every fetch in the consuming\ntask.  This allows to \"opt-out\" of the artifact prefix mechanism for\nindividual fetches.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D43535", "files": ["taskcluster/taskgraph/transforms/job/__init__.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "b9dbcc4fdabfde2fbbfb60127d690329ccbc1496", "parents": ["137971f64c25356ca3a3a6e37fa879e301a4528f"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Makoto Kato \u003cm_kato@ga2.so-net.ne.jp\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1511154 - Add junit test for location.hash setter. r=geckoview-reviewers,droeh\n\nBy bug 1563538, we don't call `onLoadRequest` when setting location.hash. So this issue is fixed by it.\n\nSo we should add geckoview-junit test for this.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D43574", "files": ["mobile/android/geckoview/src/androidTest/java/org/mozilla/geckoview/test/NavigationDelegateTest.kt"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "08669f191b51e50f7062c5f1276cb28d3576e212", "parents": ["b9dbcc4fdabfde2fbbfb60127d690329ccbc1496"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Olli Pettay \u003cOlli.Pettay@helsinki.fi\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1576783, make browser_doorhanger_bc_downloadAutoFailures_bgWin.js more resilient to when popupshown event fires, r=rstrong\n\npopupshown may get fired while waiting for closeWindow or promiseFocus to be executed.\nOther uses of runDoorhangerUpdateTest seem to be simpler and should be fine without popupShown parameter.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D43672", "files": ["toolkit/mozapps/update/tests/browser/browser_doorhanger_bc_downloadAutoFailures_bgWin.js", "toolkit/mozapps/update/tests/browser/head.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "35e44efd549df9db932881c291aa0e4ac8bf6b67", "parents": ["08669f191b51e50f7062c5f1276cb28d3576e212"], "tags": []}, {"author": "lesleynorton \u003clnorton@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1550122: Show errors in aboutLogins UI. r=MattN,fluent-reviewers,ntim,flod\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D42705", "files": ["browser/components/BrowserGlue.jsm", "browser/components/aboutlogins/AboutLoginsChild.jsm", "browser/components/aboutlogins/AboutLoginsParent.jsm", "browser/components/aboutlogins/content/aboutLogins.html", "browser/components/aboutlogins/content/aboutLogins.js", "browser/components/aboutlogins/content/components/login-item.css", "browser/components/aboutlogins/content/components/login-item.js", "browser/components/aboutlogins/tests/browser/browser.ini", "browser/components/aboutlogins/tests/browser/browser_loginItemErrors.js", "browser/locales/en-US/browser/aboutLogins.ftl"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "8f134018ed03d592cd9dc27ef641565163472bbd", "parents": ["35e44efd549df9db932881c291aa0e4ac8bf6b67"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Ting-Yu Lin \u003ctlin@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1573329 - Add web-platform reftests for multicol breaking. r=dbaron\n\nThese tests are fixed by bug 1575106,\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D43676", "files": ["testing/web-platform/meta/css/css-multicol/multicol-breaking-005.html.ini", "testing/web-platform/meta/css/css-multicol/multicol-breaking-nobackground-005.html.ini", "testing/web-platform/tests/css/css-multicol/multicol-breaking-005-ref.html", "testing/web-platform/tests/css/css-multicol/multicol-breaking-005.html", "testing/web-platform/tests/css/css-multicol/multicol-breaking-nobackground-005-ref.html", "testing/web-platform/tests/css/css-multicol/multicol-breaking-nobackground-005.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "86ef6dc7a0bce946387d5e0e066d2808f109c3d5", "parents": ["8f134018ed03d592cd9dc27ef641565163472bbd"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Toshihito Kikuchi \u003ctkikuchi@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1567219 - Add a metric to collect how many users launch a process with Admin but without UAC. r=aklotz\n\nThis patch adds a new Scalar metric `os.environment.is_admin_without_uac` that\nindicates the process is lauched with Admin privileges when UAC is turned off.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D42047", "files": ["browser/app/winlauncher/moz.build", "toolkit/components/telemetry/Scalars.yaml", "toolkit/xre/WinTokenUtils.cpp", "toolkit/xre/WinTokenUtils.h", "toolkit/xre/moz.build", "toolkit/xre/nsAppRunner.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "7cb87169e4cf83b1485f26e10f1b883fca3460da", "parents": ["86ef6dc7a0bce946387d5e0e066d2808f109c3d5"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Brindusan Cristian \u003ccbrindusan@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Backed out changeset 8f134018ed03 (bug 1550122) for bc failures at browser_loginItemErrors.js. CLOSED TREE", "files": ["browser/components/BrowserGlue.jsm", "browser/components/aboutlogins/AboutLoginsChild.jsm", "browser/components/aboutlogins/AboutLoginsParent.jsm", "browser/components/aboutlogins/content/aboutLogins.html", "browser/components/aboutlogins/content/aboutLogins.js", "browser/components/aboutlogins/content/components/login-item.css", "browser/components/aboutlogins/content/components/login-item.js", "browser/components/aboutlogins/tests/browser/browser.ini", "browser/components/aboutlogins/tests/browser/browser_loginItemErrors.js", "browser/locales/en-US/browser/aboutLogins.ftl"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "cd49de1d58ede9fc429ea6f221cbee95d1d8502e", "parents": ["7cb87169e4cf83b1485f26e10f1b883fca3460da"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Mike Hommey \u003cmh+mozilla@glandium.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1577046 - Tie extra-bindgen-flags file creation to cranelift. r=chmanchester\n\nWe only recurse into js/src/rust when jsrust is built, which it may not\nbe in Gecko builds. But cranelift, which may be enabled either way,\nneeds the extra-bindgen-flags file.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D43699", "files": ["js/src/moz.build", "js/src/rust/moz.build"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "17bb41227a5ad6e14eda7f3f3fff5b70365f9b6c", "parents": ["cd49de1d58ede9fc429ea6f221cbee95d1d8502e"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Tim Nguyen \u003cntim.bugs@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1575604 - Align the search field to the left of login-item. r=jaws\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D43683", "files": ["browser/components/aboutlogins/content/aboutLogins.css", "browser/components/aboutlogins/content/components/fxaccounts-button.css"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "f0237adbd823a9a85ddeabf9eb0e66186d8fd0db", "parents": ["17bb41227a5ad6e14eda7f3f3fff5b70365f9b6c"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Ted Campbell \u003ctcampbell@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1576865 - Add missing call to ReportOutOfMemory in LazyScriptCreationData. r=jwalden\n\nThe closedOverBinding set uses the SystemAllocPolicy so we must manually\nraise OOM exceptions.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D43650", "files": ["js/src/frontend/SharedContext.h", "js/src/jit-test/