Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D41288", "files": ["dom/serviceworkers/test/test_serviceworker_interfaces.js", "dom/tests/mochitest/general/test_interfaces.js", "dom/workers/test/test_worker_interfaces.js", "mobile/android/app/geckoview-prefs.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "b01343e4c2eb8a91be32132fafc0318d4710dfc5", "parents": ["4dd9aa1b7a94714300e74403205d4e597b5ea7ea"], "tags": []}, {"author": "James Willcox \u003csnorp@snorp.net\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1343678 - Use window context for `GeckoSessionTestRule.evaluateJS()` r=geckoview-reviewers,droeh\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D41289", "files": ["mobile/android/geckoview/src/androidTest/assets/web_extensions/test-support/test-support.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "5010684cdca410c6fceaf69a02d3a93ff607a0ea", "parents": ["b01343e4c2eb8a91be32132fafc0318d4710dfc5"], "tags": []}, {"author": "James Willcox \u003csnorp@snorp.net\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1343678 - Add WebPush support to GeckoView r=jcj,lina,agi,geckoview-reviewers,droeh,mt\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D41290", "files": ["mobile/android/components/geckoview/GeckoView.manifest", "mobile/android/components/geckoview/GeckoViewPush.js", "mobile/android/components/geckoview/GeckoViewStartup.js", "mobile/android/components/geckoview/moz.build", "mobile/android/geckoview/api.txt", "mobile/android/geckoview/src/androidTest/assets/www/push/push.html", "mobile/android/geckoview/src/androidTest/assets/www/push/push.js", "mobile/android/geckoview/src/androidTest/assets/www/push/sw.js", "mobile/android/geckoview/src/androidTest/java/org/mozilla/geckoview/test/BaseSessionTest.kt", "mobile/android/geckoview/src/androidTest/java/org/mozilla/geckoview/test/WebPushTest.kt", "mobile/android/geckoview/src/androidTest/java/org/mozilla/geckoview/test/WebPushUtils.java", "mobile/android/geckoview/src/main/java/org/mozilla/geckoview/Base64Utils.java", "mobile/android/geckoview/src/main/java/org/mozilla/geckoview/GeckoRuntime.java", "mobile/android/geckoview/src/main/java/org/mozilla/geckoview/WebPushController.java", "mobile/android/geckoview/src/main/java/org/mozilla/geckoview/WebPushDelegate.java", "mobile/android/geckoview/src/main/java/org/mozilla/geckoview/WebPushSubscription.java", "mobile/android/geckoview/src/main/java/org/mozilla/geckoview/doc-files/CHANGELOG.md", "mobile/android/geckoview_example/src/main/java/org/mozilla/geckoview_example/GeckoViewActivity.java", "mobile/android/installer/package-manifest.in", "mobile/android/modules/geckoview/GeckoViewPushController.jsm", "mobile/android/modules/geckoview/moz.build", "widget/android/Base64UtilsSupport.h", "widget/android/nsAppShell.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "619e7838ebfd94672b993d34914f3852610b2905", "parents": ["5010684cdca410c6fceaf69a02d3a93ff607a0ea"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jeff Walden \u003cjwalden@mit.edu\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1577051 - Fix an implicit-conversion-changes-value warning with new-enough clang by explicitly converting.  r=froydnj\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D43701", "files": ["mfbt/FastBernoulliTrial.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "d72f6bb552f38a54c6df3b1d48e28849da0ce189", "parents": ["619e7838ebfd94672b993d34914f3852610b2905"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jeff Walden \u003cjwalden@mit.edu\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1577065 - Fix an implicit-conversion-changes-value warning with new-enough clang in AtomicsObject.cpp by explicitly converting.  r=lth\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D43706", "files": ["js/src/builtin/AtomicsObject.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "fb03ac72bc47c9b4bd97e3277ab0cee02026aa7f", "parents": ["d72f6bb552f38a54c6df3b1d48e28849da0ce189"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Barret Rennie \u003cbarret@brennie.ca\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1510569 - Implement serializers for nsITransportSecurityInfo, nsIX509Cert, and nsIX509CertList r=froydnj,keeler,mayhemer\n\nAs part of the ongoing effort to port the nsIWebProgress events from\nRemoteWebProgress / WebProgressChild to BrowserParent / BrowserChild, we need\nto (de)serialize the nsITransportSecurityInfo instance across the IPC layer.\nThe existing code was calling `NS_SerializeToString` which has the overhead of\n(a) allocating a buffer and also performing base64 encoding/decoding. This\npatch adds `IPC::ParamTraits` implementations for `nsITransportSecurityInfo`,\n`nsIX509Certificate`, and `nsIX509CertList` that (de)serializes the params\ndirectly onto and off of the IPC message so that we don't go through the\noverhead of allocating and encoding/decoding an additional buffer.\n\nThis (de)serialization will address the performance issues present in the\ncurrent implementation.\n\nAs a side effect, I also make nsITransportSecurityInfo a builtinclass XPCOM\ninterface, since the existing serialization code was assuming it was, there is\nonly one implementation, and it is in C++.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D35090", "files": ["ipc/glue/TransportSecurityInfoUtils.cpp", "ipc/glue/TransportSecurityInfoUtils.h", "ipc/glue/moz.build", "netwerk/base/FuzzySecurityInfo.cpp", "netwerk/socket/nsITransportSecurityInfo.idl", "security/apps/moz.build", "security/certverifier/moz.build", "security/certverifier/tests/gtest/moz.build", "security/manager/ssl/TransportSecurityInfo.cpp", "security/manager/ssl/TransportSecurityInfo.h", "security/manager/ssl/moz.build", "security/manager/ssl/nsIX509Cert.idl", "security/manager/ssl/nsIX509CertList.idl", "security/manager/ssl/nsNSSCertificate.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "cecb17bd8c03f033498be5dfb3ee4fc966b38e96", "parents": ["fb03ac72bc47c9b4bd97e3277ab0cee02026aa7f"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Barret Rennie \u003cbarret@brennie.ca\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1510569 - Port onSecurityChange from WebProgressChild.jsm to C++; remove WebProgressChild r=Ehsan,ochameau\n\nThis is the last message that WebProgressChild was sending to the\nRemoteWebProgress in the parent process, so we can remove the module entirely.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D35091", "files": ["browser/base/content/test/performance/browser_startup_content.js", "devtools/client/responsive/browser/tunnel.js", "dom/interfaces/base/nsIBrowser.idl", "dom/ipc/BrowserChild.cpp", "dom/ipc/BrowserParent.cpp", "dom/ipc/BrowserParent.h", "dom/ipc/PBrowser.ipdl", "toolkit/content/browser-child.js", "toolkit/content/widgets/browser-custom-element.js", "toolkit/modules/RemoteWebProgress.jsm", "toolkit/modules/WebProgressChild.jsm", "toolkit/modules/moz.build"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "fa318eec0e7600fd9daae2e5435a07231f8049c7", "parents": ["cecb17bd8c03f033498be5dfb3ee4fc966b38e96"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Barret Rennie \u003cbarret@brennie.ca\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1510569 - Add nsIWebProgressListener2 to BrowserChild's interface map r=Ehsan\n\nThe members of nsIWebProgressListener2 were added to BrowserChild (then\nTabChild) in commit 1028814583232487b52b9c20d47e3b38dc1c288a, but the interface\nwas never added to the interface map.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D35134", "files": ["dom/ipc/BrowserChild.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "03b7cf756a7f7a0e96fe22950a41fe08a075094e", "parents": ["fa318eec0e7600fd9daae2e5435a07231f8049c7"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Barret Rennie \u003cbarret@brennie.ca\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1510569 - Use nsIPrincipal and nsIContentSecurityPolicy in WebProgressLocationChangeData directly r=nika\n\nNow that there is an {IPDL}ParamTraits implementation for nsIPrincipal* and\nnsIContentSecurityPolicy*, we need not manually transform it to/form a\nPrincipalInfo/CSPInfo ourselves.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D36637", "files": ["dom/ipc/BrowserChild.cpp", "dom/ipc/BrowserParent.cpp", "dom/ipc/PBrowser.ipdl"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "d7db6a1935ce83a21a8c90503a01f040ef6412a7", "parents": ["03b7cf756a7f7a0e96fe22950a41fe08a075094e"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Chris Manchester \u003ccmanchester@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1577049 - Provide sccache and dist-toolchains during bootstrap on Windows. r=froydnj\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D43700", "files": ["python/mozboot/mozboot/mozillabuild.py", "python/mozboot/mozboot/sccache.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "1d8bb18fa74ffc16d4726a1b312d38d967cfe445", "parents": ["d7db6a1935ce83a21a8c90503a01f040ef6412a7"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Chris Manchester \u003ccmanchester@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1572880 - Package dist-toolchains from a specific directory. r=froydnj\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D43696", "files": ["taskcluster/scripts/misc/build-dist-toolchains.sh"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "f3741f2b33822b4242cba5d4c8d6823d16ada7b5", "parents": ["1d8bb18fa74ffc16d4726a1b312d38d967cfe445"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Dorel Luca \u003cdluca@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Backed out 4 changesets (bug 1510569) for build bustage. CLOSED TREE\n\nBacked out changeset d7db6a1935ce (bug 1510569)\nBacked out changeset 03b7cf756a7f (bug 1510569)\nBacked out changeset fa318eec0e76 (bug 1510569)\nBacked out changeset cecb17bd8c03 (bug 1510569)", "files": ["browser/base/content/test/performance/browser_startup_content.js", "devtools/client/responsive/browser/tunnel.js", "dom/interfaces/base/nsIBrowser.idl", "dom/ipc/BrowserChild.cpp", "dom/ipc/BrowserParent.cpp", "dom/ipc/BrowserParent.h", "dom/ipc/PBrowser.ipdl", "ipc/glue/TransportSecurityInfoUtils.cpp", "ipc/glue/TransportSecurityInfoUtils.h", "ipc/glue/moz.build", "netwerk/base/FuzzySecurityInfo.cpp", "netwerk/socket/nsITransportSecurityInfo.idl", "security/apps/moz.build", "security/certverifier/moz.build", "security/certverifier/tests/gtest/moz.build", "security/manager/ssl/TransportSecurityInfo.cpp", "security/manager/ssl/TransportSecurityInfo.h", "security/manager/ssl/moz.build", "security/manager/ssl/nsIX509Cert.idl", "security/manager/ssl/nsIX509CertList.idl", "security/manager/ssl/nsNSSCertificate.cpp", "toolkit/content/browser-child.js", "toolkit/content/widgets/browser-custom-element.js", "toolkit/modules/RemoteWebProgress.jsm", "toolkit/modules/WebProgressChild.jsm", "toolkit/modules/moz.build"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "b9052a99c4f0d646cb06fd624cac64e2948cfb67", "parents": ["f3741f2b33822b4242cba5d4c8d6823d16ada7b5"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Ed Lee \u003cedilee@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1572515 - mach lint complains about newtab logs missing license r=dmose\n\nExclude \"built\" logs/ directory from any linting\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D41263", "files": ["tools/rewriting/ThirdPartyPaths.txt"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "215c31bbe5159f3bebe7cc4f5848ed4fb955eb44", "parents": ["b9052a99c4f0d646cb06fd624cac64e2948cfb67"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jeff Muizelaar \u003cjrmuizel@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1577190. Don't treat Mask items like Filter items in DetectContainerLayerPropertiesBoundsChange. r=nical,mstange\n\nThis is a remnant from the previous implementation of masking. That\nimplementation was replaced in bug 1447880.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D43763", "files": ["gfx/layers/wr/WebRenderCommandBuilder.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "1794ff261cf8a4d89e71c6487202955705cda61b", "parents": ["215c31bbe5159f3bebe7cc4f5848ed4fb955eb44"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Julian Descottes \u003cjdescottes@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1575766 - Set mIsDevToolsDocument on DevTools documents r=smaug\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D43639", "files": ["dom/base/Document.cpp", "dom/base/Document.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "79d597b5cd7e4a9c9f440055c1a1a62ee4046043", "parents": ["1794ff261cf8a4d89e71c6487202955705cda61b"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Julian Descottes \u003cjdescottes@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1575766 - Use chrome preferences for DevTools documents r=emilio\n\nDepends on D43639\n\nThis will avoid applying High Contrast mode colors to devtools documents even when DevTools are loaded in a frame with type=content\nThis behavior can be disabled by setting devtools.toolbox.force-chrome-prefs to false\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D43614", "files": ["layout/style/PreferenceSheet.cpp", "modules/libpref/init/StaticPrefList.yaml"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "040cb1876f196b017749fa8e0feb0c4afc96f0b4", "parents": ["79d597b5cd7e4a9c9f440055c1a1a62ee4046043"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Dorel Luca \u003cdluca@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Backed out changeset 3853d8979a55 (bug 1575240) for Devtools on devtools/client/webconsole/test/browser/browser_jsterm_inspect.js", "files": ["devtools/client/framework/toolbox.js", "devtools/client/webconsole/test/browser/browser.ini", "devtools/client/webconsole/test/browser/browser_jsterm_inspect.js", "devtools/client/webconsole/test/browser/test-simple-function.html", "devtools/client/webconsole/test/browser/test-simple-function.js", "devtools/client/webconsole/webconsole-wrapper.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "5ca811a6a88389b21477a0dc47667310615cd47d", "parents": ["040cb1876f196b017749fa8e0feb0c4afc96f0b4"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Aaron Klotz \u003caklotz@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1577061: Modify nsUpdateDriver's GetCurrentWorkingDir to accept a nsACString& argument; r=mhowell\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D43711", "files": ["toolkit/xre/nsUpdateDriver.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "5284ee6d9f6e6300e124eb6f2cb5fd83ce544402", "parents": ["5ca811a6a88389b21477a0dc47667310615cd47d"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Tom Ritter \u003ctom@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1570597 - Pass the -delayload flag to lld correctly for MinGW builds r=firefox-build-system-reviewers,mshal\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D43455", "files": ["python/mozbuild/mozbuild/frontend/emitter.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "59422c064fd1269aa29ec901e6bdf43c54ae92be", "parents": ["5284ee6d9f6e6300e124eb6f2cb5fd83ce544402"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Barret Rennie \u003cbarret@brennie.ca\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1510569 - Implement serializers for nsITransportSecurityInfo, nsIX509Cert, and nsIX509CertList r=froydnj,keeler,mayhemer\n\nAs part of the ongoing effort to port the nsIWebProgress events from\nRemoteWebProgress / WebProgressChild to BrowserParent / BrowserChild, we need\nto (de)serialize the nsITransportSecurityInfo instance across the IPC layer.\nThe existing code was calling `NS_SerializeToString` which has the overhead of\n(a) allocating a buffer and also performing base64 encoding/decoding. This\npatch adds `IPC::ParamTraits` implementations for `nsITransportSecurityInfo`,\n`nsIX509Certificate`, and `nsIX509CertList` that (de)serializes the params\ndirectly onto and off of the IPC message so that we don't go through the\noverhead of allocating and encoding/decoding an additional buffer.\n\nThis (de)serialization will address the performance issues present in the\ncurrent implementation.\n\nAs a side effect, I also make nsITransportSecurityInfo a builtinclass XPCOM\ninterface, since the existing serialization code was assuming it was, there is\nonly one implementation, and it is in C++.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D35090", "files": ["ipc/glue/TransportSecurityInfoUtils.cpp", "ipc/glue/TransportSecurityInfoUtils.h", "ipc/glue/moz.build", "netwerk/base/FuzzySecurityInfo.cpp", "netwerk/socket/nsITransportSecurityInfo.idl", "security/apps/moz.build", "security/certverifier/moz.build", "security/certverifier/tests/gtest/moz.build", "security/manager/ssl/TransportSecurityInfo.cpp", "security/manager/ssl/TransportSecurityInfo.h", "security/manager/ssl/moz.build", "security/manager/ssl/nsIX509Cert.idl", "security/manager/ssl/nsIX509CertList.idl", "security/manager/ssl/nsNSSCertificate.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "4d29b7c90a5fbcea87dd5d990504dd1bb1cd8d90", "parents": ["59422c064fd1269aa29ec901e6bdf43c54ae92be"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Barret Rennie \u003cbarret@brennie.ca\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1510569 - Port onSecurityChange from WebProgressChild.jsm to C++; remove WebProgressChild r=Ehsan,ochameau\n\nThis is the last message that WebProgressChild was sending to the\nRemoteWebProgress in the parent process, so we can remove the module entirely.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D35091", "files": ["browser/base/content/test/performance/browser_startup_content.js", "devtools/client/responsive/browser/tunnel.js", "dom/interfaces/base/nsIBrowser.idl", "dom/ipc/BrowserChild.cpp", "dom/ipc/BrowserParent.cpp", "dom/ipc/BrowserParent.h", "dom/ipc/PBrowser.ipdl", "toolkit/content/browser-child.js", "toolkit/content/widgets/browser-custom-element.js", "toolkit/modules/RemoteWebProgress.jsm", "toolkit/modules/WebProgressChild.jsm", "toolkit/modules/moz.build"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "e27459aad2c9c752b01c197f2039b0b3ba8c8e41", "parents": ["4d29b7c90a5fbcea87dd5d990504dd1bb1cd8d90"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Barret Rennie \u003cbarret@brennie.ca\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1510569 - Add nsIWebProgressListener2 to BrowserChild's interface map r=Ehsan\n\nThe members of nsIWebProgressListener2 were added to BrowserChild (then\nTabChild) in commit 1028814583232487b52b9c20d47e3b38dc1c288a, but the interface\nwas never added to the interface map.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D35134", "files": ["dom/ipc/BrowserChild.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "ca4611846475b8a2bd2032a1a963b07cec6539f5", "parents": ["e27459aad2c9c752b01c197f2039b0b3ba8c8e41"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Barret Rennie \u003cbarret@brennie.ca\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1510569 - Use nsIPrincipal and nsIContentSecurityPolicy in WebProgressLocationChangeData directly r=nika\n\nNow that there is an {IPDL}ParamTraits implementation for nsIPrincipal* and\nnsIContentSecurityPolicy*, we need not manually transform it to/from a\nPrincipalInfo/CSPInfo ourselves.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D36637", "files": ["dom/ipc/BrowserChild.cpp", "dom/ipc/BrowserParent.cpp", "dom/ipc/PBrowser.ipdl"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "ac49017fe65e926f46238e7d7b399009a0237826", "parents": ["ca4611846475b8a2bd2032a1a963b07cec6539f5"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Alexandre Poirot \u003cpoirot.alex@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1570696 - Destroy Toolbox on TabClose event for local tab targets. r=jdescottes\n\nMove disconnection message out of Toolbox class in favor of toolbox-init module\nas that is specific to Toolbox loaded in a tab.\nWe do that in order to stop automatically destroying the toolbox when the\nattached target is destroyed. This will help support switching to another target\nwhen we navigate between two documents loaded in distinct processes.\nWe will now destroy the toolboxes for local tabs only when TabClose event\nis fired.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D40233", "files": ["devtools/client/framework/toolbox-init.js", "devtools/client/framework/toolbox.js", "devtools/shared/fronts/targets/target-mixin.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "0e3a4fb87da3b39e3a15ddb9e8dd6de42f9fd1c9", "parents": ["ac49017fe65e926f46238e7d7b399009a0237826"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Kris Maglione \u003cmaglione.k@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1577263: Use memcmp for nsID::Equals. r=froydnj\n\nCompilers have gotten a lot better since the last time we tried this, and the\ngenerated SIMD code for the inlined memcmp is more efficient than our manual\ncomparison operations.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D43802", "files": ["xpcom/base/nsID.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "3e2987e01215fb9ce600074886866766da1444dd", "parents": ["0e3a4fb87da3b39e3a15ddb9e8dd6de42f9fd1c9"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Kris Maglione \u003cmaglione.k@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1576407: Part 1 - Add HadOriginalOpener flag to BrowsingContext. r=farre\n\nThis is currently only available on the outer window, but needs to move to\nBrowsingContext in order from us to remove redundant opener tracking from the\nformer.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D43690", "files": ["docshell/base/BrowsingContext.cpp", "docshell/base/BrowsingContext.h", "docshell/base/BrowsingContextFieldList.h", "dom/base/nsGlobalWindowOuter.cpp", "dom/base/nsGlobalWindowOuter.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "be7cbc61f825fdfc36b20d476bef710ef275ad73", "parents": ["3e2987e01215fb9ce600074886866766da1444dd"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Kris Maglione \u003cmaglione.k@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1576407: Part 2 - Don't set BrowsingContext opener when forcing noopener. r=farre\n\nWe currently handler this correctly for the opener stored on the outer window,\nbut not on the BrowsingContext.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D43691", "files": ["dom/ipc/ContentChild.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "08d4c25fc67068280c150f260fd8e2381eab87c9", "parents": ["be7cbc61f825fdfc36b20d476bef710ef275ad73"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Kris Maglione \u003cmaglione.k@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1576407: Part 3 - Return window opener as a WindowProxyHolder or BrowsingContext. r=farre\n\nAlso adds a legacy `GetSameProcessOpener()` method for callers which can only\ndeal with in-process windows and may need to be updated for Fission.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D43692", "files": ["docshell/base/nsDSURIContentListener.cpp", "dom/base/Document.cpp", "dom/base/nsGlobalWindowInner.cpp", "dom/base/nsGlobalWindowInner.h", "dom/base/nsGlobalWindowOuter.cpp", "dom/base/nsGlobalWindowOuter.h", "dom/base/nsPIDOMWindow.h", "dom/websocket/WebSocket.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "0ddbc451dcab431c2a1d934fa9baa5e8efc71545", "parents": ["08d4c25fc67068280c150f260fd8e2381eab87c9"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Kris Maglione \u003cmaglione.k@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1576407: Part 4 - Stop storing opener redundantly on nsGlobalWindowOuter. r=farre\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D43693", "files": ["docshell/base/BrowsingContext.h", "dom/base/nsFrameLoader.cpp", "dom/base/nsGlobalWindowInner.cpp", "dom/base/nsGlobalWindowOuter.cpp", "dom/base/nsGlobalWindowOuter.h", "dom/base/nsPIDOMWindow.h", "dom/ipc/ContentChild.cpp", "toolkit/components/windowwatcher/nsWindowWatcher.cpp", "xpfe/appshell/nsWebShellWindow.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "19bf40067233299dbe4870e3a5698ae67027dcd9", "parents": ["0ddbc451dcab431c2a1d934fa9baa5e8efc71545"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Kris Maglione \u003cmaglione.k@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1576407: Part 5 - Update test expectations to handler cross-process window.opener being available. r=farre\n\nThis also sets the fission.rebuild_frameloaders_on_remoteness_change=true\npreference for some mochitest directories which require it for cross-process\nwindow.opener to work in top-level windows, and makes a minor change to the\nhack in browser_temporary_permissions.js to keep it passing reliably in try\nruns.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D43694", "files": ["browser/base/content/test/permissions/browser_temporary_permissions.js", "dom/tests/mochitest/bugs/mochitest.ini", "dom/tests/mochitest/localstorage/mochitest.ini", "dom/tests/mochitest/sessionstorage/mochitest.ini", "dom/tests/mochitest/whatwg/mochitest.ini", "toolkit/components/extensions/test/mochitest/mochitest-common.ini"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "38e4ea4314452422fe5fcfb8b1b557201ae9c0f8", "parents": ["19bf40067233299dbe4870e3a5698ae67027dcd9"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Toshihito Kikuchi \u003ctkikuchi@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1567219 - Add a metric to collect how many users launch a process with Admin but without UAC. r=aklotz\n\nThis patch adds a new Scalar metric `os.environment.is_admin_without_uac` that\nindicates the process is lauched with Admin privileges when UAC is turned off.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D42047", "files": ["browser/app/winlauncher/moz.build", "toolkit/components/telemetry/Scalars.yaml", "toolkit/xre/WinTokenUtils.cpp", "toolkit/xre/WinTokenUtils.h", "toolkit/xre/moz.build", "toolkit/xre/nsAppRunner.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "465c399713381aae67efede22e3496602d2139b5", "parents": ["38e4ea4314452422fe5fcfb8b1b557201ae9c0f8"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Michael Cooper \u003cmcooper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1572479 pt1 - Move PreferenceExperiment migrations to NormandyMigrations.jsm r=glasserc\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D42055", "files": ["toolkit/components/normandy/NormandyMigrations.jsm", "toolkit/components/normandy/lib/PreferenceExperiments.jsm", "toolkit/components/normandy/test/browser/browser_PreferenceExperiments.js", "toolkit/components/normandy/test/browser/browser_actions_PreferenceExperimentAction.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "6d157db92bc951194c5bd528d292c84e78bbb25d", "parents": ["465c399713381aae67efede22e3496602d2139b5"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Michael Cooper \u003cmcooper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1572479 pt2 - Rename preference experiment name to slug r=rdalal\n\nNaming this field better matches the intent of the field, other actions, and\nthe schemas used by the recipes on the server. Overall it makes the code less\nconfusing, and more consistent.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D41296", "files": ["toolkit/components/normandy/NormandyMigrations.jsm", "toolkit/components/normandy/actions/PreferenceExperimentAction.jsm", "toolkit/components/normandy/content/about-studies/about-studies.js", "toolkit/components/normandy/lib/ClientEnvironment.jsm", "toolkit/components/normandy/lib/PreferenceExperiments.jsm", "toolkit/components/normandy/lib/ShieldPreferences.jsm", "toolkit/components/normandy/test/NormandyTestUtils.jsm", "toolkit/components/normandy/test/browser/browser_ClientEnvironment.js", "toolkit/components/normandy/test/browser/browser_PreferenceExperiments.js", "toolkit/components/normandy/test/browser/browser_ShieldPreferences.js", "toolkit/components/normandy/test/browser/browser_about_studies.js", "toolkit/components/normandy/test/browser/browser_actions_PreferenceExperimentAction.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "1c29b632b6eb962612767e7d2c330e46f96aeef9", "parents": ["6d157db92bc951194c5bd528d292c84e78bbb25d"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Mich