/\u003cnumber\u003e for \u003caspect-ratio\u003e. r=emilio\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D41557", "files": ["layout/style/test/test_css_parse_error_smoketest.html", "layout/style/test/test_media_queries.html", "modules/libpref/init/StaticPrefList.yaml", "servo/components/style/gecko/media_features.rs", "servo/components/style/media_queries/media_feature.rs", "servo/components/style/media_queries/media_feature_expression.rs", "testing/web-platform/meta/css/mediaqueries/aspect-ratio-005.html.ini", "testing/web-platform/meta/css/mediaqueries/aspect-ratio-006.html.ini", "testing/web-platform/tests/css/mediaqueries/aspect-ratio-001.html", "testing/web-platform/tests/css/mediaqueries/aspect-ratio-003.html", "testing/web-platform/tests/css/mediaqueries/aspect-ratio-005.html", "testing/web-platform/tests/css/mediaqueries/aspect-ratio-006.html", "testing/web-platform/tests/css/mediaqueries/test_media_queries.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "f95ee35992771a820e9ca9ccd372fd5111587b17", "parents": ["2fa81d89b660198144d8c2f98c7f5043351d2766"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Dan Minor \u003cdminor@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1554976 - Allow network functions needed by Rust mDNS responder; r=tjr\n\nThis removes these functions: bind, getaddrinfo, recvfrom, sendto, setsockopt,\nsocket from the check_networking test to allow for their use by the Rust mDNS\nresponder.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D38488", "files": ["python/mozbuild/mozbuild/action/check_binary.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "e36be9c42ef1f555859514c71f03471498817e01", "parents": ["f95ee35992771a820e9ca9ccd372fd5111587b17"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Dan Minor \u003cdminor@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1554976 - Add rust mdns library to mtransport; r=ng,dragana\n\nThis adds a mdns_service to mtransport to handle responding to mDNS queries.\nAll hostnames will be generated from UUIDs, so the responder assumes that it\nis the only responder for a hostname which is registered with it. Because of\nthis, the responder does not first make a DNS query itself to see if any other\nresponder is handling a hostname, and does not wait a random amount of time\nbefore replying, both of which are required by the specification to avoid\ncollisions with other responders.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D38489", "files": ["media/mtransport/mdns_service/Cargo.toml", "media/mtransport/mdns_service/mdns_service.h", "media/mtransport/mdns_service/src/lib.rs", "toolkit/library/rust/shared/Cargo.toml", "toolkit/library/rust/shared/lib.rs"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "b1fb21e0d6c0f456d0b38a780eefc7949daf8e7b", "parents": ["e36be9c42ef1f555859514c71f03471498817e01"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Dan Minor \u003cdminor@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1554976 - Run mach vendor rust; r=ng\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D38491", "files": ["Cargo.lock", "third_party/rust/dns-parser/.cargo-checksum.json", "third_party/rust/dns-parser/Cargo.toml", "third_party/rust/dns-parser/LICENSE-APACHE", "third_party/rust/dns-parser/LICENSE-MIT", "third_party/rust/dns-parser/README.md", "third_party/rust/dns-parser/bulk.yaml", "third_party/rust/dns-parser/examples/sync_tcp_client.rs", "third_party/rust/dns-parser/examples/sync_udp_client.rs", "third_party/rust/dns-parser/src/builder.rs", "third_party/rust/dns-parser/src/enums.rs", "third_party/rust/dns-parser/src/error.rs", "third_party/rust/dns-parser/src/header.rs", "third_party/rust/dns-parser/src/lib.rs", "third_party/rust/dns-parser/src/name.rs", "third_party/rust/dns-parser/src/parser.rs", "third_party/rust/dns-parser/src/rdata/a.rs", "third_party/rust/dns-parser/src/rdata/aaaa.rs", "third_party/rust/dns-parser/src/rdata/all.rs", "third_party/rust/dns-parser/src/rdata/axfr.rs", "third_party/rust/dns-parser/src/rdata/cname.rs", "third_party/rust/dns-parser/src/rdata/hinfo.rs", "third_party/rust/dns-parser/src/rdata/maila.rs", "third_party/rust/dns-parser/src/rdata/mailb.rs", "third_party/rust/dns-parser/src/rdata/mb.rs", "third_party/rust/dns-parser/src/rdata/mf.rs", "third_party/rust/dns-parser/src/rdata/mg.rs", "third_party/rust/dns-parser/src/rdata/minfo.rs", "third_party/rust/dns-parser/src/rdata/mod.rs", "third_party/rust/dns-parser/src/rdata/mr.rs", "third_party/rust/dns-parser/src/rdata/mx.rs", "third_party/rust/dns-parser/src/rdata/ns.rs", "third_party/rust/dns-parser/src/rdata/nsec.rs", "third_party/rust/dns-parser/src/rdata/null.rs", "third_party/rust/dns-parser/src/rdata/opt.rs", "third_party/rust/dns-parser/src/rdata/ptr.rs", "third_party/rust/dns-parser/src/rdata/soa.rs", "third_party/rust/dns-parser/src/rdata/srv.rs", "third_party/rust/dns-parser/src/rdata/txt.rs", "third_party/rust/dns-parser/src/rdata/wks.rs", "third_party/rust/dns-parser/src/structs.rs", "third_party/rust/dns-parser/vagga.yaml"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "e70a875ead243db2c7e56b006591c0f8924798e7", "parents": ["b1fb21e0d6c0f456d0b38a780eefc7949daf8e7b"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Dan Minor \u003cdminor@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1554976 - Add methods to register/unregister mDNS hostnames to StunAddrsRequestParent; r=mjf\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D38492", "files": ["media/mtransport/ipc/PStunAddrsRequest.ipdl", "media/mtransport/ipc/StunAddrsRequestParent.cpp", "media/mtransport/ipc/StunAddrsRequestParent.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "95f34f8de2c4514e366c5e5ffa33f029864a9a83", "parents": ["e70a875ead243db2c7e56b006591c0f8924798e7"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Dan Minor \u003cdminor@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1554976 - Generate mDNS addresses in nricectx; r=mjf\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D38493", "files": ["media/mtransport/ipc/StunAddrsRequestParent.h", "media/mtransport/nricectx.cpp", "media/mtransport/nricectx.h", "media/mtransport/nricemediastream.h", "media/mtransport/test/ice_unittest.cpp", "media/mtransport/test/transport_unittests.cpp", "media/mtransport/third_party/nICEr/src/ice/ice_candidate.c"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "3356f4e4828e6b171b67686bcebaf2c83b5a6fac", "parents": ["95f34f8de2c4514e366c5e5ffa33f029864a9a83"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Dan Minor \u003cdminor@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1554976 - Copy actual address to CandidateInfo in MediaTransportHandler; r=mjf\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D38494", "files": ["dom/media/webrtc/WebrtcIPCTraits.h", "media/webrtc/signaling/src/common/CandidateInfo.h", "media/webrtc/signaling/src/peerconnection/MediaTransportHandler.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "fd061900910bb5cbd2b9fe58103de3926a7ac827", "parents": ["3356f4e4828e6b171b67686bcebaf2c83b5a6fac"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Dan Minor \u003cdminor@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1554976 - Register mDNS hostname if required; r=mjf\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D38495", "files": ["media/webrtc/signaling/src/peerconnection/PeerConnectionMedia.cpp", "media/webrtc/signaling/src/peerconnection/PeerConnectionMedia.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "841a7ca50a14d523ce88999fbb493ba1dd7a874d", "parents": ["fd061900910bb5cbd2b9fe58103de3926a7ac827"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Dan Minor \u003cdminor@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1554976 - Add plumbing to enable/disable host address obfuscation; r=mjf\n\nThis only enables mDNS on OS X for now. Some versions of Windows lack mDNS\nsupport, there are some oddities with resolving IPv6 addresses on Linux, and\nAndroid has not yet been tested. All of these will be addressed in follow on\nbugs.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D38496", "files": ["dom/media/webrtc/MediaTransportParent.h", "dom/media/webrtc/PMediaTransport.ipdl", "media/mtransport/nricectx.cpp", "media/mtransport/nricectx.h", "media/mtransport/test/ice_unittest.cpp", "media/mtransport/test/transport_unittests.cpp", "media/webrtc/signaling/gtest/mediapipeline_unittest.cpp", "media/webrtc/signaling/src/peerconnection/MediaTransportHandler.cpp", "media/webrtc/signaling/src/peerconnection/MediaTransportHandler.h", "media/webrtc/signaling/src/peerconnection/MediaTransportHandlerIPC.cpp", "media/webrtc/signaling/src/peerconnection/MediaTransportHandlerIPC.h", "media/webrtc/signaling/src/peerconnection/MediaTransportParent.cpp", "media/webrtc/signaling/src/peerconnection/PeerConnectionMedia.cpp", "media/webrtc/signaling/src/peerconnection/PeerConnectionMedia.h", "modules/libpref/init/all.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "e86aa4a5ee2cb93b85e802cf912e34a32b30079f", "parents": ["841a7ca50a14d523ce88999fbb493ba1dd7a874d"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Dan Minor \u003cdminor@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1554976 - Disable host address obfuscation for simulated NAT mochitests; r=mjf\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D38497", "files": ["dom/media/tests/mochitest/test_peerConnection_basicAudioNATRelay.html", "dom/media/tests/mochitest/test_peerConnection_basicAudioNATRelayTCP.html", "dom/media/tests/mochitest/test_peerConnection_basicAudioNATRelayTLS.html", "dom/media/tests/mochitest/test_peerConnection_basicAudioNATSrflx.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "73493c9b111a2ef6a0a1cfba16d89a1a6ddf532d", "parents": ["e86aa4a5ee2cb93b85e802cf912e34a32b30079f"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Dan Minor \u003cdminor@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1554976 - Obfuscate default rtp and rtcp candidates if required; r=ng\n\nThe default RTP candidate is used to populate the c= line in SDP. Rather than\nusing the mDNS address, which sipcc can not parse, we use 0.0.0.0:9, which is\nwhat Chromium has chosen as well [1].\n\nFor RTCP, the mDNS obfuscated address is used.\n\n[1] https://webrtc.googlesource.com/src.git/+/3ae59d33a310280e2f21ed4c53849950171e48e8\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D38498", "files": ["dom/media/tests/mochitest/pc.js", "dom/media/tests/mochitest/sdpUtils.js", "media/webrtc/signaling/src/peerconnection/MediaTransportHandler.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "3d3731561f2dcaf678d35219b0a24db252ed6e71", "parents": ["73493c9b111a2ef6a0a1cfba16d89a1a6ddf532d"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Dan Minor \u003cdminor@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1554976 - Use mdns_service to generate UUIDs; r=mjf\n\nWith the move to the socket process, the UUID service is no longer available\nin nricectx. This adds a pair of helper functions to mdns_service to generate\nUUIDs and uses them to generate hostnames inside nricectx.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D42150", "files": ["Cargo.lock", "media/mtransport/mdns_service/Cargo.toml", "media/mtransport/mdns_service/mdns_service.h", "media/mtransport/mdns_service/src/lib.rs", "media/mtransport/nricectx.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "691cab7deca800994aa0f2011423b1862afd9015", "parents": ["3d3731561f2dcaf678d35219b0a24db252ed6e71"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Dan Minor \u003cdminor@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1554976 - Make mDNS service a singleton; r=mjf\n\nThe current code causes one mDNS service to be created for each PeerConnection.\nDue to Bug 1569311, the services persist until shutdown, which can lead to a\nlot of mDNS threads running on sites which use WebRTC for fingerprinting. This\nchange makes it so we start at most one mDNS service.\n\nI've filed Bug 1569955 to look at shutting down the mDNS service after the\nlast hostname is unregistered. As an alternative, if we fix Bug 1569311, we\ncould also use refcounting and stop the mDNS service after the last\nStunAddrsRequestParent is freed.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D42151", "files": ["media/mtransport/ipc/StunAddrsRequestParent.cpp", "media/mtransport/ipc/StunAddrsRequestParent.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "fa71a90e3ed05141226905f6fac21dbeb293b3d4", "parents": ["691cab7deca800994aa0f2011423b1862afd9015"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Dan Minor \u003cdminor@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1554976 - Move thread assertion inside if statement in OnLookupComplete; r=mjf\n\nChecking this assertion outside of the if statement can result in\na use-after-free in debug builds.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D42152", "files": ["media/webrtc/signaling/src/peerconnection/MediaTransportHandler.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "1383a83336f216f51add39cc57c2d5a0059bfce3", "parents": ["fa71a90e3ed05141226905f6fac21dbeb293b3d4"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Dan Minor \u003cdminor@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1554976 - Use StunAddrs to set interface for mdns_service; r=mjf\n\nThe Rust get_if_addrs library previously used does not build on Android with\nour build system. Since we're already using nICEr to determine the local\ninterface addresses, rather than fix the Rust library, we can use those\naddresses to set the interface on which mdns_service listens.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D42760", "files": ["media/mtransport/ipc/StunAddrsRequestParent.cpp", "media/mtransport/ipc/StunAddrsRequestParent.h", "media/mtransport/ipc/moz.build", "media/mtransport/mdns_service/mdns_service.h", "media/mtransport/mdns_service/src/lib.rs"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "542dfee3630a15b4a1594fba7a46cca652d79d88", "parents": ["1383a83336f216f51add39cc57c2d5a0059bfce3"], "tags": []}, {"author": "David Heiberg \u003cdheiberg@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1575263 - Change to_ to into_ to suit naming convention regarding self methods r=jgraham\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D43970", "files": ["testing/geckodriver/src/marionette.rs"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "55378cbba628e718e8228e9687a2b25cc8339eb6", "parents": ["542dfee3630a15b4a1594fba7a46cca652d79d88"], "tags": []}, {"author": "David Heiberg \u003cdheiberg@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1575263 - Move closure out of if statement r=jgraham\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D43971", "files": ["testing/geckodriver/src/capabilities.rs"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "62c8064a6be0e0aed89bbcd26ce37a7533b9e200", "parents": ["55378cbba628e718e8228e9687a2b25cc8339eb6"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Yura Zenevich \u003cyura.zenevich@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1555770 - update contrast highlighter FAIL icon to red circle with ! similar to other audit types. r=rcaliman\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D43810", "files": ["devtools/server/actors/highlighters.css", "devtools/server/actors/highlighters/xul-accessible.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "a284f570400baa5a56d262816b2f41c73b7f7892", "parents": ["62c8064a6be0e0aed89bbcd26ce37a7533b9e200"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Yura Zenevich \u003cyura.zenevich@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1555770 - update contrast FAIL icon in a11y panel sidebar checks section and in inspector color picker. r=gl\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D43811", "files": ["devtools/client/themes/accessibility-color-contrast.css"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "3295674641649322d829ececd6df91f8ec98a7a7", "parents": ["a284f570400baa5a56d262816b2f41c73b7f7892"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Yura Zenevich \u003cyura.zenevich@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1555770 - update badge icons to correspond to the score of the accessibility issue. r=fvsch\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D43812", "files": ["devtools/client/accessibility/accessibility.css", "devtools/client/accessibility/components/Badge.js", "devtools/client/accessibility/components/ContrastBadge.js", "devtools/client/accessibility/components/KeyboardBadge.js", "devtools/client/accessibility/components/TextLabelBadge.js", "devtools/client/accessibility/test/jest/components/__snapshots__/badges.test.js.snap", "devtools/client/accessibility/test/jest/components/__snapshots__/contrast-badge.test.js.snap", "devtools/client/accessibility/test/jest/components/__snapshots__/keyboard-badge.test.js.snap", "devtools/client/accessibility/test/jest/components/__snapshots__/text-label-badge.test.js.snap", "devtools/client/jar.mn", "devtools/client/themes/images/alert-tiny.svg", "devtools/client/themes/images/error-tiny.svg", "devtools/client/themes/images/info-tiny.svg"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "7a8673a38e37d3d73564b02eed72149613de04bb", "parents": ["3295674641649322d829ececd6df91f8ec98a7a7"], "tags": []}, {"author": "kanurag94 \u003ckanurag94@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1556840 - Enable more ESLint rules for image/. r=Standard8,aosmond\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D43351", "files": [".eslintrc.js", "image/test/browser/browser_bug666317.js", "image/test/browser/browser_image.js", "image/test/mochitest/animationPolling.js", "image/test/mochitest/imgutils.js", "image/test/mochitest/test_animSVGImage.html", "image/test/mochitest/test_animSVGImage2.html", "image/test/mochitest/test_animation_operators.html", "image/test/mochitest/test_bug399925.html", "image/test/mochitest/test_bug415761.html", "image/test/mochitest/test_bug435296.html", "image/test/mochitest/test_bug478398.html", "image/test/mochitest/test_bug490949.html", "image/test/mochitest/test_bug496292.html", "image/test/mochitest/test_bug552605-1.html", "image/test/mochitest/test_bug552605-2.html", "image/test/mochitest/test_bug89419-2.html", "image/test/mochitest/test_discardAnimatedImage.html", "image/test/mochitest/test_discardFramesAnimatedImage.html", "image/test/mochitest/test_has_transparency.html", "image/test/mochitest/test_image_crossorigin_data_url.html", "image/test/mochitest/test_net_failedtoprocess.html", "image/test/mochitest/test_removal_ondecode.html", "image/test/mochitest/test_removal_onload.html", "image/test/mochitest/test_staticClone.html", "image/test/unit/async_load_tests.js", "image/test/unit/test_async_notification.js", "image/test/unit/test_async_notification_404.js", "image/test/unit/test_async_notification_animated.js", "image/test/unit/test_imgtools.js", "image/test/unit/test_moz_icon_uri.js", "image/test/unit/test_private_channel.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "3be18873536a3f403c9a0cf30f06bc939103a787", "parents": ["7a8673a38e37d3d73564b02eed72149613de04bb"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Dan Mosedale \u003cdmose@mozilla.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1567924 - add newtab/messaging unit testing to taskcluster r=Mardak,ahal\n\nAdds unit tests for the Home page code and Messaging System code in browser/component/newtab into treeherder/try automation.  Currently at Tier 2, should move to Tier 1 before long.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D43562", "files": ["browser/components/newtab/bin/try-runner.js", "browser/components/newtab/karma.mc.config.js", "taskcluster/ci/source-test/node.yml"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "ee1b60bbb5103a129918f2301696a51d80bbdd16", "parents": ["3be18873536a3f403c9a0cf30f06bc939103a787"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andrei Oprea \u003candrei.br92@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1577458 - Add fluent branding files to Whats New Panel r=Mardak\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D43964", "files": ["browser/components/newtab/lib/ToolbarPanelHub.jsm"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "9f021f1c28e0fe557be7b2768d41e64456a403d2", "parents": ["ee1b60bbb5103a129918f2301696a51d80bbdd16"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Boris Zbarsky \u003cbzbarsky@mit.edu\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1575204.  Fix crash when trying to run worker runnables on a not-ready-for-it worker thread.  r=baku\n\nWe're getting crashes because either there's no CycleCollectedJSContext or it\nhas a null JSContext.  Hard to tell which, and whether this is happening\nbecause our runnable comes really early in thread setup or really late in\nthread teardown.  In either case, this is restoring the null-check that used to\nbe there in this code.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D43804", "files": ["dom/workers/WorkerRunnable.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "ff88b03d2dd92d7ecbc81f24f60a4e7ff9ddd04e", "parents": ["9f021f1c28e0fe557be7b2768d41e64456a403d2"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Ed Lee \u003cedilee@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1565555 - Set pref to enable What's New panel by default r=andreio\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D43502", "files": ["browser/app/profile/firefox.js", "browser/components/newtab/test/browser/browser_asrouter_targeting.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "aff36ef651a7705800156e86076197d8a202afa7", "parents": ["ff88b03d2dd92d7ecbc81f24f60a4e7ff9ddd04e"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Tom Ritter \u003ctom@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1577243 - Unconditionally clamp the requestAnimationFrame timestamp (and clamp/jitter it in RFP mode) r=birtles\n\nIn Bug 1387894 we created a mode for Firefox where it unconditionally clamps all timestamps to 20 microseconds. This happens if you disable privacy.reduceTimerPrecision (which is on by default) and is so we don't inadvertently leak super-high-resolution (nanosec) timestamps.\n\nAs part of that patch, we started clamping animation timestamps - which are exempted from privacy.reduceTimerPrecision because it was too difficult to get them working at the time. (We should still fix that though.)\n\nThis caused new test failures, and one of those was a comparison between document timelines and the timestamp in requestAnimationFrame. we were not clamping the timestamp in requestAnimationFrame under the logic that it fires in predictable intervals.\n\nHowever discussions about the WPT change we made to 'fix' the now-broken comparison https://github.com/web-platform-tests/wpt/pull/18172 and https://github.com/web-platform-tests/wpt/pull/18357 showed me that document.timeline is supposed to be slaved to the requestAnimationFrame timestamp (or vice versa.)\n\nThe correct fix is therefore to unconditionally clamp the requestAnimationFrame timestamp AND the document.timeline timestamp. In doing so we also start clamping/jittering the requestAnimationFrame timestamp in Resist Fingerprinting mode, so that might cause some new/unexpected behaviors for that mode we should watch out for.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D43788", "files": ["layout/base/nsRefreshDriver.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "565a897065e0deb97864b7635bfb0185e88c4048", "parents": ["aff36ef651a7705800156e86076197d8a202afa7"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Tom Ritter \u003ctom@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1577243 - Backed out changeset cae99e27ccdd, restoring document.timeline and rAF timestamp comparisons r=birtles\n\nDepends on D43788\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D43789", "files": ["dom/animation/test/document-timeline/test_document-timeline.html", "testing/web-platform/tests/web-animations/timing-model/timelines/document-timelines.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "02bfa4baa2edd2d1c9417018c4cbd85e99d15aa8", "parents": ["565a897065e0deb97864b7635bfb0185e88c4048"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Matthew Noorenberghe \u003cmozilla@noorenberghe.ca\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1574812 - Don't try...catch routeMessageToTarget, only the sendAsyncMessage. r=Mardak\n\nAs far as I can tell the try...catch was originally added around various sendAsyncMessage calls but then when some logic got moved to a helper, the try...catch didn't move along with it. This try...catch made it very annoying to debug an issue with bug 1570372 because it swallowed errors that were getting thrown. It doesn't seem like a good idea to swallow all errors for large pieces of code.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D43863", "files": ["browser/components/newtab/lib/ASRouter.jsm"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "fb40acd1ac7fa2460762eb7af466645e3054be20", "parents": ["02bfa4baa2edd2d1c9417018c4cbd85e99d15aa8"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Mark Banner \u003cstandard8@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1562922 - Implement handling a separate private default engine via nsISearchService.defaultPrivateEngine. r=daleharvey\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D42956", "files": ["toolkit/components/search/SearchService.jsm", "toolkit/components/search/SearchUtils.jsm", "toolkit/components/search/tests/xpcshell/head_search.js", "toolkit/components/search/tests/xpcshell/test_defaultPrivateEngine.js", "toolkit/components/search/tests/xpcshell/test_list_json_searchdefault.js", "toolkit/components/search/tests/xpcshell/test_notifications.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "8d8222618be18cf199fe8c31f213c26d8c4b2126", "parents": ["fb40acd1ac7fa2460762eb7af466645e3054be20"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Mark Banner \u003cstandard8@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1562922 - Handle removing the currently set default private search engine. r=daleharvey\n\nDepends on D42956\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D42957", "files": ["toolkit/components/search/SearchService.jsm", "toolkit/components/search/tests/xpcshell/test_currentEngine_fallback.js", "toolkit/components/search/tests/xpcshell/test_defaultEngine_fallback.js", "toolkit/components/search/tests/xpcshell/xpcshell.ini"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "fd259cdfd3f12d146af5f3b756a55e8659761d78", "parents": ["8d8222618be18cf199fe8c31f213c26d8c4b2126"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Mark Banner \u003cstandard8@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1562922 - If the default private search engine is different to normal mode, it should default to second in the sorted list. r=daleharvey\n\nDepends on D42957\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D43091", "files": ["toolkit/components/search/SearchService.jsm", "toolkit/components/search/tests/xpcshell/test_list_json_searchorder.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "93e8ce4c2a59392b71b9263f48479e1138a71eb0", "parents": ["fd259cdfd3f12d146af5f3b756a55e8659761d78"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Mark Banner \u003cstandard8@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1562922 - Add more tests to ensure the private search engine is correctly loaded from settings. r=daleharvey\n\nDepends on D43091\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D43092", "files": ["toolkit/components/search/tests/xpcshell/data/list.json", "toolkit/components/search/tests/xpcshell/data1/engine1/manifest.json", "toolkit/components/search/tests/xpcshell/data1/engine2/manifest.json", "toolkit/components/search/tests/xpcshell/data1/list.json", "toolkit/components/search/tests/xpcshell/test_list_json_locale.js", "toolkit/components/search/tests/xpcshell/test_list_json_no_private_default.js", "toolkit/components/search/tests/xpcshell/xpcshell.ini"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "d4fa68b6082945c60fb06af4eb3394eaeeb30e86", "parents": ["93e8ce4c2a59392b71b9263f48479e1138a71eb0"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Mark Banner \u003cstandard8@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1562926 - Use the default private search engine in the address bar. r=daleharvey\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D43244", "files": ["browser/base/content/browser.js", "browser/components/urlbar/tests/browser/browser.ini", "browser/components/urlbar/tests/browser/browser_action_searchengine.js", "browser/components/urlbar/tests/browser/browser_urlbarPlaceholder.js", "toolkit/components/places/PlacesSearchAutocompleteProvider.jsm", "toolkit/components/places/UnifiedComplete.jsm"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "2cb6309ecb2323d2519577bdb6cb5b0fa1225e36", "parents": ["d4fa68b6082945c60fb06af4eb3394eaeeb30e86"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Mark Banner \u003cstandard8@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1562929 - Use the default private search engine in the context menu. r=daleharvey\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D43771", "files": ["browser/base/content/browser-context.inc", "browser/base/content/browser.js", "browser/base/content/nsContextMenu.js", "browser/components/search/test/browser/browser.ini", "browser/components/search/test/browser/browser_contextSearchTabPosition.js", "browser/components/search/test/browser/browser_contextmenu.js", "browser/components/search/test/browser/browser_google_behavior.js", "browser/components/search/test/browser/browser_searchEngine_behaviors.js", "browser/components/search/test/browser/mozsearch/mozsearch-engine-private/manifest.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "3ab80bbb5b170871af2d9e595fd17c5716f13334", "parents": ["2cb6309ecb2323d2519577bdb6cb5b0fa1225e36"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andreea Pavel \u003capavel@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1544810 - test disabled on linux64 and macosx 10.14 r=gbrown\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D43974", "files": ["browser/components/originattributes/test/browser/browser.ini"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "399d210c5a19f919249949f5fb60ffbf66d0cc87", "parents": ["3ab80bbb5b170871af2d9e595fd17c5716f13334"], "tags": []}, {"author": "David Heiberg \u003cdheiberg@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1575263 - Allow clippy double option, remove redundant let binding r=jgraham\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D43976", "files": ["testing/geckodriver/marionette/src/common.rs", "testing/geckodriver/marionette/src/message.rs"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "89a456a830022193716a0d3d04e30945930f81dc", "parents": ["399d210c5a19f919249949f5fb60ffbf66d0cc87"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Nicolas Chevobbe \u003cnchevobbe@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1534445 - Use same colors as webconsole warning messages in settings panel deprecation label. r=rcaliman .\n\nIn order to do this properly, we create new variable in\nvariables.css that hold the same values as the console-warning-*\nvariables we have in webconsole.css.\nWe take this as an opportunity to replace the box shadow on\nthe deprecation label by an outline. I think this was done\nso the border doesn't take additional height, and outline\nseems perfect for this job.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D43933", "files": ["devtools/client/framework/options-panel.css", "devtools/client/themes/variables.css", "devtools/client/themes/webconsole.css"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "6b78b362900bc8e0a5f4289cae027f4d8a47f0b5", "parents": ["89a456a830022193716a0d3d04e30945930f81dc"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Alexander Surkov \u003csurkov.alexander@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1574819 - Bookmarks Menu Button popup doesn't auto-open on drag enter r=mak\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D43801", "files": ["browser/base/content/browser-places.js", "browser/components/places/PlacesUIUtils.jsm"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "32bc8be194acef156fa4ef70ee9a7aa5c826e15b", "parents": ["6b78b362900bc8e0a5f4289cae027f4d8a47f0b5"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Matthew Noorenberghe \u003cmozilla@noorenberghe.ca\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1577180 - Get a profile before accessing BrowserGlue in test_getPotentialBreachesByLoginGUID.js. r=jaws\n\nI'm not sure of the exact cause since that would require doing a local Windows beta build and the getService error doesn't indicate what failed inside the component. I mostly guessed that this was the problem by looking at other tests which do the same thing.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D43899", "files": ["browser/components/aboutlogins/tests/unit/test_getPotentialBreachesByLoginGUID.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "716ad5a4347ec6ee6cdcc7d16b95da5e4ad7e8d2", "parents": ["32bc8be194acef156fa4ef70ee9a7aa5c826e15b"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andreas Pehrson \u003capehrson@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1507193 - Don't leave dangling js promises after seeking. r=jya\n\nOnly SeekToNextFrame cares about promises, but prior to this patch the common\nmethod HTMLMediaElement::Seek() would always return a promise.\n\nWhen the caller was not SeekToNextFrame (e.g., SetCurrentTime, FastSeek), the\npromise would end up *not* being exposed. When later rejected, we would catch\nthis and write an error to the js console.\n\nThis patch lifts the handling of the promise out of Seek() and into\nSeekToNextFrame() so that we avoid creating promises that would not get exposed\nto js.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D42511", "files": ["dom/html/HTMLMediaElement.cpp", "dom/html/HTMLMediaElement.h", "dom/media/MediaDecoder.cpp", "dom/media/MediaDecoder.h", "dom/media/MediaDecoderOwner.h", "testing/web-platform/meta/media-source/mediasource-seek-beyond-duration.html.ini", "testing/web-platform/meta/media-source/mediasource-seek-during-pending-seek.html.ini"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "03d9cfc6375de4a2708183ba8920670057e16fde", "parents": ["716ad5a4347ec6ee6cdcc7d16b95da5e4ad7e8d2"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Johann Hofmann \u003cjhofmann@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1576072 - Backed out changeset 0a7463d82e5f. r=timhuang\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D43948", "files": ["browser/base/content/browser-siteIdentity.js", "browser/base/content/test/permissions/browser_permissions.js", "browser/components/controlcenter/content/identityPanel.inc.xul", "browser/themes/shared/controlcenter/panel.inc.css"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "8761f39863afde4e9a27cb8afac788eb723ed919", "parents": ["03d9cfc6375de4a2708183ba8920670057e16fde"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Johann Hofmann \u003cjhofmann@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1576072 - Backed out changeset 93ae831e2fb9. r=timhuang\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D43949", "files": ["browser/themes/shared/identity-block/identity-block.inc.css"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "6b7bd6cb5ce0cb0776215116ad1f0cd4d2b0b44a", "parents": ["8761f39863afde4e9a27cb8afac788eb723ed919"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Johann Hofmann \u003cjhofmann@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1576072 - Add a new icon for granted permissions in the identity block + panel. r=nhnt11\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D43950", "files": ["browser/base/content/browser.xhtml", "browser/components/controlcenter/content/identityPanel.inc.xul", "browser/locales/en-US/chrome/browser/browser.dtd", "browser/themes/shared/controlcenter/panel.inc.css", "browser/themes/shared/identity-block/identity-block.inc.css", "browser/themes/shared/identity-block/permissions.svg", "browser/themes/shared/jar.inc.mn"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "4c2f7afa73da98e626db22ab8108d11b915d5760", "parents": ["6b7bd6cb5ce0cb0776215116ad1f0cd4d2b0b44a"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Nicolas Chevobbe \u003cnchevobbe@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1577431 - Cleanup Browser Console when closing its window. r=ochameau.\n\nWe  store the created DebuggerClient when opening the Browser Console\nso we can close it when closing the Browser Console window.\nThe Browser Console window `unload` event listener is moved out of\nthe BrowserConsole class to the BrowserConsoleManager, so we can close\nthe DebuggerClient when the window is closed (plus it makes more sense\nto have it here since that's where we create the window).\n\nFinally, functions that were inlined in toggleBrowserConsole are moved\nas method of the BrowserConsoleManager for clarity.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D43930", "files": ["devtools/client/webconsole/browser-console-manager.js", "devtools/client/webconsole/browser-console.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "9ba13ab83751e14ac5c7465abbd9eb6296ffc5e6", "parents": ["4c2f7afa73da98e626db22ab8108d11b915d5760"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Nicolas Chevobbe \u003cnchevobbe@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1572484 - Add a mochitest for expanding content-originated logged object in browser console. r=Honza.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D43266", "files": ["devtools/client/webconsole/test/browser/browser.ini", "devtools/client/webconsole/test/browser/browser_console_content_object.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "4766eb7d938c42a17b31d2a7af48d5724582859d", "parents": ["9ba13ab83751e14ac5c7465abbd9eb6296ffc5e6"], "tags": []}, {"author": "L. David Baron \u003cdbaron@dbaron.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1576972 - Keep lastRealFrame up-to-date even when we skip empty text frames. r=jfkthame\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D43885", "files": ["layout/base/crashtests/1576972-1.html", "layout/base/crashtests/crashtests.list", "layout/base/nsBidiPresUtils.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "696c78a89f827c1345bed59fdc786c9b412d01cd", "parents": ["4766eb7d938c42a17b31d2a7af48d5724582859d"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jared Wein \u003cjwein@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1576271 - Logins with no username should show '(no username)' in the login-item view when not editing. r=MattN,fluent-reviewers,flod\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D43334", "files": ["browser/components/aboutlogins/content/components/login-item.js", "browser/components/aboutlogins/tests/chrome/test_login_item.html", "browser/locales/en-US/browser/aboutLogins.ftl"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "8f4bcd61ad953f6a08447ef40f08b037c22e5140", "parents": ["696c78a89f827c1345bed59fdc786c9b412d01cd"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jared Wein \u003cjwein@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1572478 - Don't prompt for master password when re-rendering the login-item. r=MattN\n\nWe should only prompt for master password when copying a password, or when changing from a hidden to revealed password.\n\nThis patch maintains the revealed state when going from readonly to edit mode of the login. When leaving edit mode, whether through cancel or save, the revealed state is reset.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D43883", "files": ["browser/components/aboutlogins/content/components/login-item.js", "browser/components/aboutlogins/tests/browser/browser_updateLogin.js", "browser/components/aboutlogins/tests/chrome/test_login_item.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "d01e6a3eea5ca1c9e91ca4440a2edc35804f481f", "parents": ["8f4bcd61ad953f6a08447ef40f08b037c22e5140"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jared Wein \u003cjwein@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1576735 - Canceling the create login form when no logins are in the list should revert to the previous view. r=MattN\n\nIf there are no stored logins, the Cancel button is hidden.\nIf there are visible stored logins, clicking the Cancel button will exit and move to the first login in the list.\nIf there are no visible stored logins, clicking the Cancel button will reset the search filter, exit, and move to the first login in the list.\n\nThis patch also fixes a race condition where we could end up with multiple observer notifications if about:logins was loaded multiple times very quickly.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D43544", "files": ["browser/components/aboutlogins/AboutLoginsParent.jsm", "browser/components/aboutlogins/content/aboutLogins.js", "browser/components/aboutlogins/content/components/login-filter.js", "browser/components/aboutlogins/content/components/login-item.css", "browser/components/aboutlogins/content/components/login-list.js", "browser/components/aboutlogins/tests/browser/browser_createLogin.js", "testing/mochitest/BrowserTestUtils/ContentTaskUtils.jsm"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "0bd14a48e5b8ba743292f475cc597d27783d30d5", "parents": ["d01e6a3eea5ca1c9e91ca4440a2edc35804f481f"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Gabriel Luong \u003cgabriel.luong@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1577282 - Part 1: Move the requires before the constants and format the markup. r=Maliha\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D43978", "files": ["devtools/client/shared/widgets/Spectrum.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "0bff78d1b4663da55d1499529c40916387c54d10", "parents": ["0bd14a48e5b8ba743292f475cc597d27783d30d5"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Gabriel Luong \u003cgabriel.luong@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1577282 - Part 2: Move functions outside of the Spectrum prototype. r=Maliha\n\nDepends on D43978\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D43979", "files": ["devtools/client/shared/widgets/Spectrum.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "075e1be3e7ff66a4d759919a1e1317786347ae1b", "parents": ["0bff78d1b4663da55d1499529c40916387c54d10"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Gabriel Luong \u003cgabriel.luong@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1577282 - Part 3: Convert Spectrum to ES6 Class. r=Maliha\n\nDepends on D43979\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D43980", "files": ["devtools/client/shared/test/browser_spectrum.js", "devtools/client/shared/widgets/Spectrum.js", "devtools/client/shared/widgets/tooltip/SwatchColorPickerTooltip.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "a0612783d2b4571d4527fd3406d78af65a61eee8", "parents": ["075e1be3e7ff66a4d759919a1e1317786347ae1b"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Agi Sferro \u003cagi@sferro.dev\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1577314 - Enforce @TimeoutMillis in tests. r=snorp\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D43827", "files": ["mobile/android/geckoview/src/androidTest/java/org/mozilla/geckoview/test/rule/GeckoSessionTestRule.java"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "b52fcec4698720b4f28be22e5b0ce1d462db3978", "parents": ["a0612783d2b4571d4527fd3406d78af65a61eee8"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Emma Malysz \u003cemalysz@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1576677, removes message property from all ACTORS in BrowserGlue.jsm and ActorManagerParent.jsm r=mconley\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D43484", "files": ["browser/components/BrowserGlue.jsm", "toolkit/modules/ActorManagerParent.jsm"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "5014bc0af0ebc034fd4f257a2f0