u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1577318 - Stop using GrayText for #identity-icon-labels and .urlbar-label, and clean up #identity-icon fill color rules. r=johannh\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D43936", "files": ["browser/themes/shared/identity-block/identity-block.inc.css"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "1973d4f4c3a2eb392c366cbb89443aa9ba904350", "parents": ["4a0e19c276b3cf7094ca8e0dc791a6f6bda04ea6"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Johann Hofmann \u003cjhofmann@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1577324 - Always style the error code field in error pages as a link. r=nhnt11\n\nThe way that we're setting this now actually makes it impossible for this not to be a link, AFAICS.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D44055", "files": ["browser/themes/shared/aboutNetError.css"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "71f0bf2aee9b7643446a83a7aef67d704eb373a9", "parents": ["1973d4f4c3a2eb392c366cbb89443aa9ba904350"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jonathan Watt \u003cjwatt@jwatt.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1564788. Remove unnecessary null check from PrintPreviewUserEventSuppressor::HandleEvent. r=masayuki\n\nMost other overrides of nsIDOMEventListener::HandleEvent don't null check\naEvent at all.  This method should never be called without an event.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D38906", "files": ["layout/printing/PrintPreviewUserEventSuppressor.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "dd6e8cc3c3d4d155c69de00c8357d45a8e5d94b7", "parents": ["71f0bf2aee9b7643446a83a7aef67d704eb373a9"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Nihanth Subramanya \u003cnhnt11@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1577459 - Update Tracking Content description copy and remove Site Still Broken copy. r=johannh\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D44127", "files": ["browser/components/controlcenter/content/protectionsPanel.inc.xul", "browser/locales/en-US/chrome/browser/browser.dtd"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "4de1432a4cd729d10c005f43a92944c6145a8afd", "parents": ["dd6e8cc3c3d4d155c69de00c8357d45a8e5d94b7"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Brindusan Cristian \u003ccbrindusan@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Backed out 5 changesets (bug 1543782) for devtools failures on browser_rules_completion-on-empty.js.\n\nBacked out changeset d7b6b036d777 (bug 1543782)\nBacked out changeset 2081fd72fd28 (bug 1543782)\nBacked out changeset 703a2947c350 (bug 1543782)\nBacked out changeset 822638e9789a (bug 1543782)\nBacked out changeset cb477711fa64 (bug 1543782)", "files": ["devtools/client/inspector/rules/new-rules.js", "devtools/client/inspector/rules/test/browser.ini", "devtools/client/inspector/rules/test/browser_rules_completion-on-empty.js", "devtools/client/inspector/rules/test/browser_rules_completion-shortcut.js", "devtools/client/inspector/rules/test/browser_rules_gridline-names-autocomplete.js", "devtools/client/inspector/rules/test/head.js", "devtools/client/inspector/rules/views/text-property-editor.js", "devtools/client/shared/inplace-editor.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "c5ad764d28355ec966faaed00e94076fd39a9a4a", "parents": ["4de1432a4cd729d10c005f43a92944c6145a8afd"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jan de Mooij \u003cjdemooij@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1573674 part 1 - Move JSContext::setPendingException to the cpp file. r=Yoric\n\nThere's a lot of code and this path is slow enough that a non-inlined call isn't\ngoing to be an issue.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D43583", "files": ["js/src/vm/JSContext-inl.h", "js/src/vm/JSContext.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "9f3f9eee5143c535bf7da5fee2f3d016798fdf4c", "parents": ["c5ad764d28355ec966faaed00e94076fd39a9a4a"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jan de Mooij \u003cjdemooij@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1573674 part 2 - Don't report OOM exceptions to Nightly-only error interceptor hook. r=Yoric\n\nDepends on D43583\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D43584", "files": ["js/src/vm/JSContext.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "1aa2c382c4ec27ed4f4ef560eff38fa4f8c91be4", "parents": ["9f3f9eee5143c535bf7da5fee2f3d016798fdf4c"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Gerald Squelart \u003cgsquelart@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1577650 - Stop using `using namespace std` in Gecko Profiler - r=canaltinova\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D44076", "files": ["mozglue/baseprofiler/core/VTuneProfiler.cpp", "tools/profiler/core/VTuneProfiler.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "f05189f8caefa446a9c112bc40ab027f5cf654e3", "parents": ["1aa2c382c4ec27ed4f4ef560eff38fa4f8c91be4"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Johann Hofmann \u003cjhofmann@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1577636 - Update some strings for the identity panel. r=nhnt11\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D44130", "files": ["browser/base/content/browser-siteIdentity.js", "browser/components/controlcenter/content/identityPanel.inc.xul", "browser/locales/en-US/chrome/browser/browser.dtd", "browser/locales/en-US/chrome/browser/browser.properties"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "69032a22c6ef425d373c70e297997507014fa81b", "parents": ["f05189f8caefa446a9c112bc40ab027f5cf654e3"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jonathan Kew \u003cjkew@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1577669 - Cast to uint32_t before left-shifting byte value by 24 bits. r=jrmuizel\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D44132", "files": ["gfx/cairo/libpixman/src/pixman-sse2.c"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "b541c2200a393c11f33dcf47e0f065dcfc2b0c2f", "parents": ["69032a22c6ef425d373c70e297997507014fa81b"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Emilio Cobos \u00c1lvarez \u003cemilio@crisal.io\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1577749 - Fix check_sccache_version when using RUSTC_WRAPPER. r=jwatt\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D44139", "files": ["build/moz.configure/toolchain.configure"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "cd8cfdc6b5b3d0ce775afda2bb3c443451baa20f", "parents": ["b541c2200a393c11f33dcf47e0f065dcfc2b0c2f"], "tags": []}, {"author": "championshuttler \u003cshivams2799@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1574609 - Fix telemetry/telemetry path component in firefox-source-docs. r=ahal\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D44110", "files": ["toolkit/components/telemetry/moz.build", "toolkit/docs/index.rst", "tools/docs/redirects.yml"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "24031facb68fd1a99c71d87a90416b9890dba484", "parents": ["cd8cfdc6b5b3d0ce775afda2bb3c443451baa20f"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jon Coppeard \u003cjcoppeard@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1571008 - Make background alloc kind selection less confusing r=jandem\n\nThis renames a couple of functions to hopefully make their intent clearer add adds comments and assertions.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D44014", "files": ["js/src/builtin/Array.cpp", "js/src/gc/AllocKind.h", "js/src/gc/GCTrace.cpp", "js/src/gc/ObjectKind-inl.h", "js/src/vm/EnvironmentObject.cpp", "js/src/vm/JSObject.cpp", "js/src/vm/NativeObject-inl.h", "js/src/vm/ProxyObject.cpp", "js/src/vm/Shape.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "62533f3df2b6bd4590cc20d56c7ee8b8272dd0db", "parents": ["24031facb68fd1a99c71d87a90416b9890dba484"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Patrick Brosset \u003cpbrosset@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1576484 - Bail out of getParentGridElement when the element is \u003chtml\u003e; r=rcaliman\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D44017", "files": ["devtools/client/inspector/rules/test/browser_rules_inactive_css_grid.js", "devtools/server/actors/utils/inactive-property-helper.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "3d56bbe0a97d36440e3d724cfb74815caf3caead", "parents": ["62533f3df2b6bd4590cc20d56c7ee8b8272dd0db"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Nathan Froyd \u003cfroydnj@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1577326 - use std::unique_ptr in the crashreporter client; r=gsvelto\n\n`std::auto_ptr` is going away in C++17, so we might as well switch to\nthe approved thing now.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D44042", "files": ["toolkit/crashreporter/client/crashreporter.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "a62c0eb6faa60c5cb1720a76641ee3a6269d6388", "parents": ["3d56bbe0a97d36440e3d724cfb74815caf3caead"], "tags": []}, {"author": "D\u00e3o Gottwald \u003cdao@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1577742 - Inrease the megabar's z-index so it overlaps the tab overflow indicators. r=harry\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D44135", "files": ["browser/themes/shared/urlbar-searchbar.inc.css"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "21483daf4d9db7fbeae739085f842d522ad38d0f", "parents": ["a62c0eb6faa60c5cb1720a76641ee3a6269d6388"], "tags": []}, {"author": "D\u00e3o Gottwald \u003cdao@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1577752 - Use padding-block and padding-inline for the urlbar's one-off search button adjustments. r=harry\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D44141", "files": ["browser/themes/shared/urlbar-autocomplete.inc.css"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "3e9155a5cd2404bb61c2c4a6d0d708a290078953", "parents": ["21483daf4d9db7fbeae739085f842d522ad38d0f"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jonathan Kew \u003cjkew@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1576846 - Fix the content-process's use of mAliasTable to temporarily record alternate font family names on Windows. r=jwatt\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D43746", "files": ["gfx/thebes/SharedFontList.cpp", "gfx/thebes/gfxPlatformFontList.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "3acfcd288f567c09ce806ce144f48447bd01b661", "parents": ["3e9155a5cd2404bb61c2c4a6d0d708a290078953"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Sylvestre Ledru \u003csledru@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1577726 - Ride along: Remove a directory which doesn't exist anymore r=andi\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D44145", "files": ["tools/rewriting/ThirdPartyPaths.txt"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "3249ffd467a2483bd2c7ab470e49c1399d6c9833", "parents": ["3acfcd288f567c09ce806ce144f48447bd01b661"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Sylvestre Ledru \u003csledru@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1577726 - Ride along: explicit the file names (lz4.c instead of lz4.*) r=andi\n\nDepends on D44145\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D44146", "files": ["tools/rewriting/ThirdPartyPaths.txt"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "d5b2fb678a67e5273b19de560a7750b68d503258", "parents": ["3249ffd467a2483bd2c7ab470e49c1399d6c9833"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Sebastian Hengst \u003carchaeopteryx@coole-files.de\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1577363 - Set dom/security/test/general/mochitest.ini as passing with fission. r=Ehsan\n\nIt got set as failing in bug 1576814 but passes after bug 1576316 added back fission-incompatible code.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D44113", "files": ["dom/security/test/general/mochitest.ini"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "565713650a1b46d1e1f4dc69f61ec2c758ac1f10", "parents": ["d5b2fb678a67e5273b19de560a7750b68d503258"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andreas Pehrson \u003capehrson@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1577495 - Use a single SharedDummyStream per HTMLMediaElement. r=karlt\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D43982", "files": ["dom/html/HTMLMediaElement.cpp", "dom/html/HTMLMediaElement.h", "dom/media/MediaDecoder.cpp", "dom/media/MediaDecoder.h", "dom/media/MediaDecoderStateMachine.cpp", "dom/media/MediaDecoderStateMachine.h", "dom/media/MediaStreamGraph.h", "dom/media/mediasink/OutputStreamManager.cpp", "dom/media/mediasink/OutputStreamManager.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "6bf377de1057cd0bbdbe888e8e20693f926c7d03", "parents": ["565713650a1b46d1e1f4dc69f61ec2c758ac1f10"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andreas Pehrson \u003capehrson@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1576938 - Add crashtest. r=karlt\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D44019", "files": ["dom/media/tests/crashtests/1576938.html", "dom/media/tests/crashtests/crashtests.list"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "e830fea4c442f23ee56f4c33ddb42666df0f6e7a", "parents": ["6bf377de1057cd0bbdbe888e8e20693f926c7d03"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andreas Pehrson \u003capehrson@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1576938 - Allow a live MediaStreamTrack to be created with a destroyed input stream. r=karlt\n\nThis is a valid use case when cloning a MediaStreamTrack, if the source track of\nthe clone has had its input stream destroyed out-of-band and that change hasn't\nbeen asynchronously communicated to the source track yet, i.e., it's still live.\n\nDepends on D44019\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D44020", "files": ["dom/media/MediaStreamTrack.cpp", "dom/media/MediaStreamTrack.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "2f4ccf9252b971b8dc165ea86848d91a5d274acf", "parents": ["e830fea4c442f23ee56f4c33ddb42666df0f6e7a"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andreas Pehrson \u003capehrson@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1576938 - Make MediaInputPort::Init work on an already-disconnected port. r=karlt\n\nDepends on D44020\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D44021", "files": ["dom/media/MediaStreamGraph.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "087b063910da4bb4d7d346e4a75404bf55de6da7", "parents": ["2f4ccf9252b971b8dc165ea86848d91a5d274acf"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Emilio Cobos \u00c1lvarez \u003cemilio@crisal.io\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1577745 - Remove dead version of nsStyleDisplay::IsOriginalDisplayInlineOutside. r=mats\n\nSVG Text stuff doesn't support abspos or anything like that, so it's not like it\nis useful.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D44136", "files": ["layout/generic/ReflowInput.cpp", "layout/style/nsStyleStruct.h", "layout/style/nsStyleStructInlines.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "f7ff76e196bdb37607020bf9fc5db4ef8818fcf6", "parents": ["087b063910da4bb4d7d346e4a75404bf55de6da7"], "tags": []}, {"author": "David Teller \u003cdteller@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1572365 - Removing magic header from Context decoder;r=arai\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D41169", "files": ["js/src/frontend/BinASTTokenReaderContext.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "ef2853ccdc1162c25b9e36018c73dfd3eb3ea894", "parents": ["f7ff76e196bdb37607020bf9fc5db4ef8818fcf6"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Emily McMinn \u003cemily@mcminn.ca\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1551588 - Added a tab stop to the \"info\" and \"dismiss\" buttons in the FxA Bookmark Panel Message r=k88hudson\n\nThe Bookmark Panel Message now has tab stops on the info button, message dismiss icon, and message link, as well as all form fields and CTA buttons.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D42692", "files": ["browser/base/content/browser.xhtml", "browser/themes/shared/places/editBookmarkPanel.inc.css"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "089d52d6ad36eb3122cdfc6eacd2a6e0e5c42613", "parents": ["ef2853ccdc1162c25b9e36018c73dfd3eb3ea894"], "tags": []}, {"author": "David Major \u003cdmajor@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1577528 - Remove hardcoded clang version in ccov mozconfigs r=froydnj\n\nSo that we don't have to keep bumping them by hand with every compiler upgrade.\n\nThis pattern was taken from the other uses of https://searchfox.org/mozilla-central/search?q=CLANG_LIB_DIR&case=true\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D43990", "files": ["browser/config/mozconfigs/linux64/code-coverage", "browser/config/mozconfigs/macosx64/code-coverage"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "87d437ca92a92161ad2d3dba4c4947ab16ca1ec4", "parents": ["089d52d6ad36eb3122cdfc6eacd2a6e0e5c42613"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Emilio Cobos \u00c1lvarez \u003cemilio@crisal.io\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1577191 - Crashtest.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D44155", "files": ["dom/base/crashtests/1577191.html", "dom/base/crashtests/crashtests.list"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "8e5bc0fc04e2666865aa2f126a372ed62c4b0fe7", "parents": ["87d437ca92a92161ad2d3dba4c4947ab16ca1ec4"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jan de Mooij \u003cjdemooij@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1577565 - Fix patchNopToCall and patchCallToNop to flush the icache on ARM and MIPS. r=lth\n\nThe ARM64 code was already doing this correctly.\n\nThis also affects Wasm debugger breakpoints but it's not clear to me why\nfuzzing didn't find the same issue there.\n\nWe are considering doing icache flushing on mprotect, it would eliminate\nthese issues.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D44140", "files": ["js/src/jit/arm/MacroAssembler-arm.cpp", "js/src/jit/mips-shared/MacroAssembler-mips-shared.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "9e00286ac2a6b8953e216dbf904fa2aa5914853f", "parents": ["8e5bc0fc04e2666865aa2f126a372ed62c4b0fe7"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Nihanth Subramanya \u003cnhnt11@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1574111 - Improve the definition of ThirdPartyCookies.isDetected. r=johannh\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D43464", "files": ["browser/base/content/browser-siteProtections.js", "browser/base/content/test/trackingUI/browser_trackingUI_cookies_subview.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "6e6f9cf6ea5861630bf0570ae6667660b583bc70", "parents": ["9e00286ac2a6b8953e216dbf904fa2aa5914853f"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Razvan Caliman \u003crcaliman@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1577467 - Remove obsolete iframe container for DevTools animation inspector; r=daisuke\n\nThe animation inspector is [loaded on demand by the inspector](https://searchfox.org/mozilla-central/rev/8ea946dcf51f0d6400362cc1d49c8d4808e`eacf1/devtools/client/inspector/inspector.js#937-942) as a sidebar panel via an `InspectorPanel` instance. The iframe container from index.xhtml seems to be a leftover from a time where the animation inspector was loaded differently.\n\nNo failing tests after removing iframe. Is this ok to cleanup?\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D43951", "files": ["devtools/client/inspector/components/InspectorTabPanel.css", "devtools/client/inspector/index.xhtml", "devtools/client/themes/inspector.css"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "a07e1432deaab8acf7a4a090f2365cfcd86c5d22", "parents": ["6e6f9cf6ea5861630bf0570ae6667660b583bc70"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Emilio Cobos \u00c1lvarez \u003cemilio@crisal.io\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1576229 - Account for user stylesheets for Shadow DOM invalidation. r=jwatt\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D43992", "files": ["layout/style/test/mochitest.ini", "layout/style/test/test_user_sheet_shadow_dom.html", "servo/components/style/invalidation/element/state_and_attributes.rs"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "19e21bdb79cbfdc5b3a9c2323d3fcb6e28f159cc", "parents": ["a07e1432deaab8acf7a4a090f2365cfcd86c5d22"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Nathan Froyd \u003cfroydnj@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1576941 - be more careful about success when running dsymutil; r=nalexander\n\nVarious artifacts we produce don't actually have debug symbols, but\n`llvm-dsymutil` will happily run on them and produce garbage for\n`dump_syms` to look at.  Let's not do that.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D43772", "files": ["toolkit/crashreporter/tools/symbolstore.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "4ea7cebd11a3738600b4d4356984db4e5f4fe234", "parents": ["19e21bdb79cbfdc5b3a9c2323d3fcb6e28f159cc"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Nathan Froyd \u003cfroydnj@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1576748 - make symbolstore.py complain loudly if expected output isn't found; r=nalexander\n\nThis change surfaces errors faster, and ensures that we don't silently\nend up with empty crashreporter symbols if `dump_syms` can't run for\nsome reason.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D43520", "files": ["toolkit/crashreporter/tools/symbolstore.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "9d271586649f004ee40ce35fbe510c567d54c1f0", "parents": ["4ea7cebd11a3738600b4d4356984db4e5f4fe234"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Erica Wright \u003cewright@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1577465 - Protection report string revisions. r=fluent-reviewers,johannh,flod\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D44024", "files": ["browser/components/protections/content/lockwise-card.js", "browser/components/protections/content/monitor-card.js", "browser/components/protections/content/protections.html", "browser/components/protections/content/protections.js", "browser/components/protections/test/browser/browser_protections_lockwise.js", "browser/components/protections/test/browser/browser_protections_monitor.js", "browser/locales/en-US/browser/protections.ftl"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "ec88018fd94e5e6d013b722186c95f20ecbb615b", "parents": ["9d271586649f004ee40ce35fbe510c567d54c1f0"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Emilio Cobos \u00c1lvarez \u003cemilio@crisal.io\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1570759 - Enable the optimization to not flush for fixed margin values. r=jwatt\n\nAs noted this changes behavior, but it's unclear per\nhttps://github.com/w3c/csswg-drafts/issues/2328 what behavior is correct, and\nour behavior is inconsistent depending on whether there's any percentage\ninvolved.\n\nThis matches other browsers so it's pretty low risk I'd say.\n\nThe test starts passing without changes to the test, but given the CSSWG issue I\nmade the test not rely on the optimization.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D43754", "files": ["layout/style/nsComputedDOMStyle.cpp", "testing/web-platform/meta/css/css-box/parsing/margin-computed.html.ini", "testing/web-platform/tests/css/css-box/parsing/margin-computed.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "7fa833ff0b1c7880dbba9cd9b6014ad88bed5b67", "parents": ["ec88018fd94e5e6d013b722186c95f20ecbb615b"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andreas Pehrson \u003capehrson@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1577734 - Don't unset mGraphTimeOffset in MediaStreamRenderer. r=padenot\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D44158", "files": ["dom/html/HTMLMediaElement.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "11104935922576fa9d6c2e7ae73a1b09ebab5477", "parents": ["7fa833ff0b1c788