_urlbar_keyed_search.js", "browser/base/content/test/performance/browser_urlbar_search.js", "browser/components/search/content/search-one-offs.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "f4a413a2ebbbe0ed89f94575c27a230a7e126955", "parents": ["7c06991f7561f5be48f3f5342e7c881923aace8a"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Erica Wright \u003cewright@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1578544 - Resize margins and heights. r=johannh a=lizzard\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D44533", "files": ["browser/components/protections/content/protections.css"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "df2eccb35ba5595e44939baa532c35dbf874d9e3", "parents": ["f4a413a2ebbbe0ed89f94575c27a230a7e126955"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Julien Wajsberg \u003cfelash@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1578354 - Remove the obsolete condition so that JS frames are now properly filtered in in the call tree r=gregtatum a=lizzard\n\nBug 1557789 added categories to all JS frames, so as a result JS frames\nwhere all filtered out because of the condition removed in this patch.\nThis condition is basically a premature optimization, removing it\nshouldn't bring any behavior difference.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D44803", "files": ["devtools/client/performance/modules/logic/frame-utils.js", "devtools/client/performance/test/browser_perf-tree-view-02.js", "devtools/client/performance/test/browser_perf-tree-view-03.js", "devtools/client/performance/test/browser_perf-tree-view-04.js", "devtools/client/performance/test/browser_perf-tree-view-06.js", "devtools/client/performance/test/helpers/synth-utils.js", "devtools/client/performance/test/unit/test_frame-utils-02.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "eb147c90d7dbc7de17580f60cd6c1d5f3bbf0931", "parents": ["df2eccb35ba5595e44939baa532c35dbf874d9e3"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Gijs Kruitbosch \u003cgijskruitbosch@gmail.com\u0