\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1438364 - ensure settings data is cleared during uninstall r=robwu a=pascalc\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D43553", "files": ["toolkit/components/extensions/ExtensionSettingsStore.jsm", "toolkit/components/extensions/test/xpcshell/test_ext_extensionSettingsStore.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "1bf5461e31ac03d15c22b2e2bbe8e16c94cbeb29", "parents": ["9279d511042719439162694d4a44cfd8db0f1464"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Julian Descottes \u003cjdescottes@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1578373 - Stop using window.top in devtools/client/shared/widgets/Graphs.js r=julienw a=pascalc\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D45448", "files": ["devtools/client/shared/widgets/Graphs.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "d6318c213e71015dacfceefadcd1f103d7d8109f", "parents": ["1bf5461e31ac03d15c22b2e2bbe8e16c94cbeb29"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Daosheng Mu \u003cdaoshengmu@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1581988 - Making VR display enumerationCompleted be false when doing enumeration. r=kip a=pascalc\n\nIf VR process haven't launched yet, we couldn't get available VR displays and its states, so we need to make enumationCompleted to be false, and ask it do the enumeration again.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D46238", "files": ["gfx/vr/VRManager.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "8b150aa4228aa08a685796e6364a8458d0864b89", "parents": ["d6318c213e71015dacfceefadcd1f103d7d8109f"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Dana Keeler \u003cdkeeler@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "bug 1577944 - avoid calling CERT_NewTempCertificate in NSSCertDBTrustDomain::GetCertTrust for enterprise certificates r=jcj,kjacobs a=pascalc\n\nCalling CERT_NewTempCertificate on an enterprise certificate is inefficient\nbecause NSS tries (and fails) to find a copy of that certificate in its internal\ndata structures (which includes querying softoken, which involves hitting the\ndisk). We can avoid doing so for these certificates in\nNSSCertDBTrustDomain::GetCertTrust because we already know what trust values\nthey should have (after checking the relevant blocklists).\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D45588", "files": ["security/certverifier/NSSCertDBTrustDomain.cpp", "security/certverifier/NSSCertDBTrustDomain.h", "security/manager/ssl/CSTrustDomain.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "64258962f918054811dbb496d19a0d11d36e30ea", "parents": ["8b150aa4228aa08a685796e6364a8458d0864b89"], "tags": []}], "date": 1569240325, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null, null], "user": "malexandru@mozilla.com"}, "12024": {"changesets": [{"author": "Byron Campen [:bwc] \u003cdocfaraday@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1577719: Init r_log in the c'tor, to simplify things. r=mjf, a=RyanVM\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D45463", "files": ["media/webrtc/signaling/src/peerconnection/MediaTransportHandler.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "57e9358e143d4cd6ddbbaa4b4d37249fe57923b6", "parents": ["64258962f918054811dbb496d19a0d11d36e30ea"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Byron Campen [:bwc] \u003cdocfaraday@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1581950: Prevent nr_ice_component_insert_pair from leaking. r=mjf, a=RyanVM\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D46231", "files": ["media/mtransport/third_party/nICEr/src/ice/ice_component.c"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "99c61c3e15a19886b667b02dc157c7ea2a3d731a", "parents": ["57e9358e143d4cd6ddbbaa4b4d37249fe57923b6"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Nathan Froyd \u003cfroydnj@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1581145 - update sfntly to master; r=jfkthame, a=RyanVM\n\nThis update brings in severa