n-bump DONTBUILD\n\nsk -\u003e 5c2bbeb48c6b", "files": ["mobile/locales/l10n-changesets.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "64f03c4c6cbf4936b12eb301068334e50401474e", "parents": ["c61b1562b030fbdec369f8e3b9ae63766affff23"], "tags": []}, {"author": "L10n Bumper Bot \u003crelease+l10nbumper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "no bug - Bumping Firefox l10n changesets r=release a=l10n-bump DONTBUILD\n\nhe -\u003e 186e19a18f56\nsk -\u003e 5c2bbeb48c6b", "files": ["browser/locales/l10n-changesets.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "c7d8dc9abc33820f1595a9c08afce02f69c0c88a", "parents": ["64f03c4c6cbf4936b12eb301068334e50401474e"], "tags": []}], "date": 1569355241, "git_changesets": [null, null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "12036": {"changesets": [{"author": "Dan Minor \u003cdminor@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1581193 - Fix devicechange event on Windows; r=achronop a=lizzard\n\nThis restores the code for generating devicechange events that was\naccidentally removed as part of updating the Windows video capture code\nin Bug 1552755.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D46033", "files": ["media/webrtc/trunk/webrtc/modules/video_capture/windows/device_info_ds.cc", "media/webrtc/trunk/webrtc/modules/video_capture/windows/device_info_ds.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "c0bd917aeecce986301440bff852a4e7a463969f", "parents": ["c7d8dc9abc33820f1595a9c08afce02f69c0c88a"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Alex Chronopoulos \u003cachronop@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1581806 - Trigger devicechange event for audio and video input devices only. r=dminor a=lizzard\n\nAfter Bug 1581193 devicechange notifications were triggered with any device change, not just video and audio devices. This patch limits down the notifications to only video and audio input devices change.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D46147", "files": ["media/webrtc/trunk/webrtc/modules/video_capture/windows/device_info_ds.cc", "media/webrtc/trunk/webrtc/modules/video_capture/windows/device_info_ds.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "7354577a6ec48116d491bd44b139b5cf8e4385b0", "parents": ["c0bd917aeecce986301440bff852a4e7a463969f"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Logan Smyth \u003cloganfsmyth@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1580645 - Ensure that node removal only removes mutation BPs in subtree. r=davidwalsh a=lizzard\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D44296", "files": ["devtools/server/actors/inspector/walker.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "30741417bbc39489400d0fd3d261033f7026418b", "parents": ["7354577a6ec48116d491bd44b139b5cf8e4385b0"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Lina Cambridge \u003clina@yakshaving.ninja\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1582377 - Don't recreate existing bookmarks mirror indexes in schema migrations. r=tcsc a=lizzard\n\nDowngrading a profile and syncing downgrades the bookmarks mirror\nschema version, but leaves the new indexes in place. This causes the\nmigration logic to throw an \"index already exists\" error on upgrade.\nThe fix is to add an `IF NOT EXISTS`, to avoid recreating the index.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D46434", "files": ["toolkit/components/places/SyncedBookmarksMirror.jsm", "toolkit/components/places/tests/sync/test_bookmark_mirror_migration.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "db46e193a5c6b129453bf8e44466f8a31a3e80ad", "parents": ["30741417bbc39489400d0fd3d261033f7026418b"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Lina Cambridge \u003clina@yakshaving.ninja\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1582377 - Catch invalid URLs caused by bookmarks mirror tag query rewriting. r=tcsc a=lizzard\n\nRewriting a tag query might produce an invalid URL; for example, if the\ntag name contains special characters. We don't currently URL-encode tag\nfolder names in queries (bug 1449939), so our only option is to flag the\nquery as invalid. This should fix the \"\u003cURL\u003e is not a valid URL\" and\n\"url is null\" errors seen in telemetry.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D46435", "files": ["toolkit/components/places/SyncedBookmarksMirror.jsm", "toolkit/components/places/tests/sync/test_bookmark_kinds.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "23e4deb8581f5d6f88b198810be5b1415b4e4f5f", "parents": ["db46e193a5c6b129453bf8e44466f8a31a3e80ad"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Erica Wright \u003cewright@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1582265 - Add animations to the bar graph. r=johannh a=lizzard\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D46364", "files": ["browser/components/protections/content/protections.css", "browser/components/protections/content/protections.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "4a93e4ecabd66469ef8fae959d7b737bad647634", "parents": ["23e4deb8581f5d6f88b198810be5b1415b4e4f5f"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Harry Twyford \u003chtwyford@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1581096 - Align search panel engine icon with clock icons. r=dao a=lizzard\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D45938", "files": ["browser/themes/shared/searchbar.inc.css"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "d7a88a4fb29501dd22616ad0d39c4e6fd6b9f097", "parents": ["4a93e4ecabd66469ef8fae959d7b737bad647634"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Masayuki Nakano \u003cmasayuki@d-toybox.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1582010 - Make `IMEContentObserver` always recompute selection range after sending text change notification r=m_kato a=lizzard\n\n`IMEContentObserver` sends selection change notification only when it receives\na DOM `Selection` change notification received.  However, selection range in\nplaintext offset may be changed when changing previous content of caret is\nchanged.  In this case, currently we notify IME of only text change and\nthat causes IME keep caching selection offsets in previous content.  This\ncauses IME queries character rect out of bounds.  Therefore, even if\n`IMEContentObserver` hasn't received DOM `Selection` change notification,\nit should recompute selection range and if it's changed, it should notify\nIME of selection change too.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D46251", "files": ["dom/events/IMEContentObserver.cpp", "widget/tests/window_composition_text_querycontent.xul"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "a552d3955e14a2e2c98f9c56aed0d0a1438e5bf3", "parents": ["d7a88a4fb29501dd22616ad0d39c4e6fd6b9f097"], "tags": []}, {"author": "James Teh \u003cjteh@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1582323: When a file input has DOM focus, focus the browse button inside it for a11y. r=MarcoZ a=lizzard\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D46386", "files": ["accessible/html/HTMLFormControlAccessible.cpp", "accessible/html/HTMLFormControlAccessible.h", "accessible/tests/mochitest/events/test_focus_controls.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "3ca86ab994bff98de8a5cc93c8d75b48ce7bcb03", "parents": ["a552d3955e14a2e2c98f9c56aed0d0a1438e5bf3"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Nihanth Subramanya \u003cnhnt11@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1582763 - [Protections Panel] Remove blue badge from shield and toggle when TP is disabled. r=johannh a=lizzard\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D46618", "files": ["browser/base/content/browser-siteProtections.js", "browser/themes/shared/controlcenter/panel.inc.css", "browser/themes/shared/identity-block/identity-block.inc.css"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "69a1bd55264869c5a53100ee20020fb727bc722b", "parents": ["3ca86ab994bff98de8a5cc93c8d75b48ce7bcb03"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Johann Hofmann \u003cjhofmann@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1581415 - Add missing wrap attributes to toolbarbuttons in the protections panel. r=nhnt11 a=lizzard\n\nSee bug 1564077 on why this is necessary.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D46767", "files": ["browser/components/controlcenter/content/protectionsPanel.inc.xul"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "8258a9e19157e6367d04e4ac0d7bcc4776afb8f5", "parents": ["69a1bd55264869c5a53100ee20020fb727bc722b"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Bryce Seager van Dyk \u003cbvandyk@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1578143 - Prevent TrackBuffersManager attempting to access buffered ranges if none exist when evicting data. r=jya a=lizzard\n\nIt appears possible for data eviction to take place despite the manager not\ncurrently having any buffered ranges. This shouldn't happen, but if it can if\nthe buffers have become full with 0 duration data. This patch attempts to\nmitigate that case by removing all coded frames. This prevents a bad access on\nthe buffered ranges and should clear up space in the buffers to append more\ndata.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D44711", "files": ["dom/media/mediasource/TrackBuffersManager.cpp", "dom/media/mediasource/TrackBuffersManager.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "d12a3157212a37629fe31e1b272445110c9b5660", "parents": ["8258a9e19157e6367d04e4ac0d7bcc4776afb8f5"], "tags": []}], "date": 1569360989, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null], "user": "rgurzau@mozilla.com"}, "12037": {"changesets": [{"author": "Olli Pettay \u003cOlli.Pettay@helsinki.fi\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1518410, try to make browser_UsageTelemetry_uniqueOriginsVisitedInPast24Hours.js fail a bit less likely, r=Ehsan, a=test-only\n\nThere is still another related bug 1579591, which this may make a bit less likely, since that seems to be timing dependent, but\nthe patch is not trying to fix that.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D46242", "files": ["browser/modules/test/browser/browser_UsageTelemetry_uniqueOriginsVisitedInPast24Hours.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "b903d1db9c3437f16021c1fca5e61c4127b79a38", "parents": ["d12a3157212a37629fe31e1b272445110c9b5660"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Julian Descottes \u003cjdescottes@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1565858 - aboutdebugging sidebar test should use longer timings in debug builds r=daisuke, a=test-only\n\nWhen running in debug builds, the test will use the default timings instead of the faster ones.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D46476", "files": ["devtools/client/aboutdebugging/test/browser/browser_aboutdebugging_sidebar_connection_state.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "d02ca673ea9e10bd7e09c76aefe0e84f0fbbced5", "parents": ["b903d1db9c3437f16021c1fca5e61c4127b79a38"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Ting-Yu Lin \u003ctlin@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1514584 - Remove non-existing img src in column-balancing-overflow-003.html and its reference. r=dholbert, a=test-only\n\n`image-short.png` never exists in the first place when this test was\nintroduced, so the intermittent happens when the test file shows a\nbroken image icon and the reference file without, or the other way\naround.\n\nI believe the `\u003cimg\u003e` is served as a monolithic element to overflow\n`\u003cdiv class=\"short\"\u003e`. Use an empty src should suffice.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D46640", "files": ["layout/reftests/columns/column-balancing-overflow-003.html", "layout/reftests/columns/column-balancing-overflow-003.ref.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "de5bf1307b2cf8f594a59302edccdb3e59211785", "parents": ["d02ca673ea9e10bd7e09c76aefe0e84f0fbbced5"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Ehsan Akhgari \u003cehsan@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1582053 - Disable the remote settings server in web extension xpcshell tests. r=kmag, a=test-only\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D46498", "files": ["toolkit/components/extensions/ExtensionXPCShellUtils.jsm"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "d74c55e7aa31c199aaa2f97b1e4a201a57a17805", "parents": ["de5bf1307b2cf8f594a59302edccdb3e59211785"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Ehsan Akhgari \u003cehsan@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1582053 - Disable the remote settings database creation instead of the server in web extension xpcshell tests; r=kmag, a=test-only\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D46664", "files": ["toolkit/components/extensions/ExtensionXPCShellUtils.jsm", "toolkit/components/extensions/test/xpcshell/test_proxy_userContextId.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "cc63f94852463ec2eb9c340bdacfb908f0671a78", "parents": ["d74c55e7aa31c199aaa2f97b1e4a201a57a17805"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Olli Pettay \u003cOlli.Pettay@helsinki.fi\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1582655, try to make browser_test_feature_preferencereads.js less racy and let browser_test_feature_jsallocations.js to run a bit longer, r=whawkins, a=test-only\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D46865", "files": ["tools/profiler/tests/browser/browser_test_feature_jsallocations.js", "tools/profiler/tests/browser/browser_test_feature_preferencereads.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "9dd1edbf897eb02ff20660577054696489a49d94", "parents": ["cc63f94852463ec2eb9c340bdacfb908f0671a78"], "tags": []}], "date": 1569363873, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null, null], "user": "ryanvm@gmail.com"}, "12038": {"changesets": [{"author": "L10n Bumper Bot \u003crelease+l10nbumper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", 