], "tags": []}], "date": 1569598391, "git_changesets": [null, null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "12064": {"changesets": [{"author": "Mozilla Releng Treescript \u003crelease+treescript@mozilla.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "No bug - Tagging 6f62baa8eaaa21c5423f0a0aad04cf202e85e372 with DEVEDITION_70_0b10_RELEASE a=release CLOSED TREE DONTBUILD", "files": [".hgtags"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "a8664ce0d8dd13db6de946ed30fa7a8261d5c2fb", "parents": ["6d1188a6d15f7051eb27f4a76a29b98ea539fea3"], "tags": []}], "date": 1569598584, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "12065": {"changesets": [{"author": "Marco Bonardo \u003cmbonardo@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1578856 - browser.fixup.dns_first_for_single_words and the keyword-uri-fixup UI are broken. r=adw a=lizzard\n\nIn the Quantum Bar it's usually the urlbar code that decides whether a search\nstring should be visited or searched. if dns_first_for_single_words is set,\nwe can't make a final decision, because that depends on a dns lookup. For now\nwe don't want to duplicate the docshell code, also because we must keep the\nold behavior functioning for cases where the urlbar value is set without input.\n\nSimilarly, when the docshell decides to search for a single word host, and a\ndns lookup resolves it, it also shows a prompt asking the user if he meant to\nvisit it instead of searching. Because the urlbar skips the docshell decision\nmaking, we must manually call the fixup prompt code from the urlbar.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D45743", "files": ["browser/base/content/browser.js", "browser/components/urlbar/UrlbarInput.jsm", "browser/components/urlbar/UrlbarPrefs.jsm", "browser/components/urlbar/UrlbarUtils.jsm", "browser/components/urlbar/tests/browser/browser.ini", "browser/components/urlbar/tests/browser/browser_dns_first_for_single_words.js", "browser/components/urlbar/tests/browser/browser_urlbarSearchSingleWordNotification.js", "docshell/test/browser/browser_uriFixupAlternateRedirects.js", "docshell/test/browser/browser_uriFixupIntegration.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "5d81ca85a83ce6067d09de8e2f576ce10d717fdc", "parents": ["a8664ce0d8dd13db6de946ed30fa7a8261d5c2fb"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Marco Bonardo \u003cmbonardo@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1581635 - disable browser_dns_first_for_single_words.js for linux verify due to intermittent failures. r=adw a=lizzard\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D46776", "files": ["browser/components/urlbar/tests/browser/browser.ini"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "60460b7ebca0579b204b466256e347db4a73618d", "parents": ["5d81ca85a83ce6067d09de8e2f576ce10d717fdc"], "tags": []}, {"author": "James Teh \u003cjteh@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1316965: Give file inputs an a11y role of GROUPING so screen readers report their label when focus enters them. r=MarcoZ a=lizzard\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D46375", "files": ["accessible/html/HTMLFormControlAccessible.cpp", "accessible/tests/mochitest/elm/test_HTMLSpec.html", "accessible/tests/mochitest/role/test_general.html", "accessible/tests/mochitest/tree/test_filectrl.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "256e2d1a8ed57f4c08ce5b2d6a8942171d3fdd96", "parents": ["60460b7ebca0579b204b466256e347db4a73618d"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jan Horak \u003cjhorak@redhat.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1581773 - Fix disappearing bookmark edit panel when choosing folder under Wayland; r=stransky a=lizzard\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D46440", "files": ["widget/gtk/nsWindow.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "97f7c310e2473491261387e9cf16503ecab98bcf", "parents": ["256e2d1a8ed57f4c08ce5b2d6a8942171d3fdd96"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Makoto Kato \u003cm_kato@ga2.so-net.ne.jp\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1580669 - Backed out bug 1545393 until bug 1582363 is fixed. r=snorp a=lizzard\n\nAccessibility caret receives incorrect mouse move event, so I revert `layout.reflow.synthMouseMove` preference until bug 1582363 is fixed.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D46439", "files": ["mobile/android/app/mobile.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "42b9ba8aa2c2a573c7f87495ae27921682612d49", "parents": ["97f7c310e2473491261387e9cf16503ecab98bcf"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Emilio Cobos \u00c1lvarez \u003cemilio@crisal.io\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1579585 - Use fallible allocation for stylesheet invalidation. r=jwatt a=lizzard\n\nIf the sets get too big we cannot allocate anything else, we'll just empty them\nand invalidate the whole document.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D46828", "files": ["servo/components/hashglobe/src/hash_set.rs", "servo/components/style/invalidation/stylesheets.rs"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "edac1bbc6240c4a7e6729c073731eacc797fcb39", "parents": ["42b9ba8aa2c2a573c7f87495ae27921682612d49"], "tags": []}, {"author": "D\u00e3o Gottwald \u003cdao@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1577740 - Set custom disabled text color for urlbar and searchbar results since native graytext is too faint on Mac. r=harry a=lizzard\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D46933", "files": ["browser/themes/linux/browser.css", "browser/themes/osx/browser.css", "browser/themes/windows/browser.css", "toolkit/components/extensions/test/browser/browser_ext_themes_autocomplete_popup.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "3aaaeea6dd03afc04cc06274e5d8cd6065c7c147", "parents": ["edac1bbc6240c4a7e6729c073731eacc797fcb39"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Johann Hofmann \u003cjhofmann@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1564248 - Re-add 