ide the What's New button from the toolbar when in Customize mode r=Gijs a=lizzard\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D46964", "files": ["browser/base/content/browser.css"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "b75075fa08c99dc8ad8a9c829a9f72e48d6c4a4c", "parents": ["14706dc0f3aa5ebf6754ea7c97b6e9ab395f787d"], "tags": []}, {"author": "D\u00e3o Gottwald \u003cdao@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1581753 - Improve one-off search button layout in narrow windows. r=mak a=lizzard\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D47270", "files": ["browser/themes/shared/urlbar-autocomplete.inc.css"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "337981f64cc634ccd1ef3fbdee930bb776b32948", "parents": ["b75075fa08c99dc8ad8a9c829a9f72e48d6c4a4c"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Luca Greco \u003clgreco@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1578447 - Fix storage panel ui not refreshing on changes to items with string keys parsable as JSON. r=miker a=lizzard\n\nIn /devtools/client/storage/ui.js, handleChangedItems and handleDeletedItems should only JSON.parse string keys related to the indexedDB and Cache actors.\n\nThe string keys used by all the other storage actors are expected to be a simple string keys, and their valid values include strings that can be successfully parsed as JSON (e.g. \"123\" or \"null\" are both valid keys for the storage items related to the localStorage, extensionStorage etc.).\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D45197", "files": ["devtools/client/storage/test/browser_storage_dynamic_updates_localStorage.js", "devtools/client/storage/test/storage-updates.html", "devtools/client/storage/ui.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "a1ddf2dcc0e4020358fda4599335694959fce981", "parents": ["337981f64cc634ccd1ef3fbdee930bb776b32948"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Nihanth Subramanya \u003cnhnt11@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": 